title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt
margarine in large pan.
Blend in brown sugar and add salt.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk,
let
it
come
to a boil and remove from heat.
Add vanilla and mix well.
If frosting is too thick to spread, add small amount of milk.

title: lemon surprise pudding
directions: Combine flour, margarine, sugar (3/4 cup), lemon juice and peel.
Add beaten egg yolks, then add milk, a little at a time. In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar (1/4 cup).
Fold egg whites into first mixture.
Pour into 6 lightly greased custard cups.
Place cups in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When baked, it has cakelike portion on top and creamy pudding under it.

title: hillbilly bleu cheese dressing
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, Bleu cheese, crumbled, cottage cheese, garlic powder, sugar and sour cream, thoroughly mixing ingredients until creamy.
Slowly add milk, thinning the dressing to a creamy consistency.
Mix very well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Great on salads or as veggie dip.

title: vegetable burger
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine. Mix with other ingredients; divide into 4 equal balls.
Put on nonstick baking sheet; flatten.
Bake until golden brown and puffy, about 15 minutes.
Turn; bake 3 to 5 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: pinch me cake
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
In large bowl, mix 3/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nuts.
Coat biscuits, a few at a time, in mixture.
Bring to boil 1 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and oleo.
Place half of the biscuits in greased Bundt pan and pour half of the syrup over them.
Then add the remaining biscuits and pour remaining syrup over them.
Sprinkle remaining dry ingredients over top and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in an oblong dish at 375° until brown and done.
No icing needed.

title: caramel cream sandwich cookies
directions: Cream butter and gradually add brown sugar; cream well.
Blend in egg yolk, then add flour.
Stir until mixture forms a dough. Chill if necessary.
Shape into balls size of a marble.
Place on ungreased baking sheets and flatten to 1/8-inch thickness with palm of hand.
Make a design by pressing with fork in one direction. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes until cookies begin to brown.
Remove from sheet while warm.
Place flat sides of 2 cookies together with frosting.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain grease.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, basil and oregano.
(Can add more oregano and basil to taste.)
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Take bottoms of buns and place on cookie sheet and tops of buns, upside down on cookie sheet. (All white parts of buns facing up.)
Spread beef mixture over top of the buns.
Then sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and either bake or broil until cheese is melted, approximately 5 to 10 minutes.

title: creamy mushroom and sausage stew
directions: Take the sausage and cut into 1-inch chunks.
This can be fixed in a crock-pot or in large Dutch oven on top of the stove, then add the rest of the ingredients that you desire.
Cook slowly until all the vegetables are done.
Very good for a crowd.

title: spam casserole
directions: Mix together Spam and potatoes.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350°, covered, until potatoes are tender.

title: fruity slaw(for diabetics)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a non-aluminum bowl.
Toss well. Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Toss well and drain before serving.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine water, tomato sauce and veggies. Bring to boil and then simmer, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Stir in soup mix; bring to boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.

title: sydney's favorite apple pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir into apples.
Turn into pastry shell.
Combine remaining flour and sugar and cut into butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
If the pie browns too quickly, cover the edges with foil.

title: mexican build-up
directions: Crumble beef into skillet.
Brown; add onion.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Bring to boil, then simmer until rice is done and mixture is thick (about 40 minutes).

title: tortellini
directions: Mix all ingredients and leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: chinese food
directions: Saute in oil the onion, celery and mushrooms.
Add turkey, bouillon cube and juice of mushrooms, plus water to make 1/2 cup. Mix together the cornstarch, soy sauce and water; stir into mixture until thick.
Add bean sprouts.
Put over rice, noodles or chow mein noodles.
Can use beef or pork instead of turkey.

title: saltine candy
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Put a single layer of saltines on foil.
Melt 2 sticks of butter and then add brown sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Then bake at 350°
for 5 minutes.
Spread melted chocolate
bits over mixture.
Put in freezer until firm, then cut.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Do not need to precook the noodles.
Grease baking dish. Combine spinach, Ricotta, 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese, egg, salt, pepper and oregano; mix well.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of large lasagna pan.
Place 1/3 of noodles over sauce. Spread 1/2 of spinach cheese mix.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles, spaghetti sauce and 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour 1 cup water into sauce jars, shake and pour around edges of dish.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Freezes well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll into balls and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: gram's crisp molasses cookies
directions: Mix molasses and sugar; add to shortening, then add soda and boiling water mixture.
Add flour, salt, ginger and cream of tartar.
Knead and let set awhile in refrigerator.
Roll to desired thickness, cut and bake at 350°.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar and meal and cream well.
Then add one egg at a time and beat thoroughly after each addition.
Add vinegar, vanilla and milk.
Beat thoroughly.
Pile in an unbaked pastry shell.
Place in an oven preheated to 400°. After 10 minutes, reduce heat to 325° and continue cooking for an additional 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli fine.
Cook in half of broth and add salt to taste.
Make paste with melted butter and flour.
Add milk slowly and cook to thicken.
Puree broccoli mix in blender and return to kettle.
Add milk mixture along with remaining broth to broccoli mixture.
Simmer to thicken.

title: party pink pineapple punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Combine juices and sugar.
Stir well. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Garnish with cherries and pineapple chunks, if desired.
Yield:
32 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Drain fruit.
Arrange slices and maraschino cherry halves on the sugar mixture.
Mix cake as directed on the label with 2/3 cup water, 3 eggs and 1/2 cup of butter or margarine.
Do not substitute fruit juice for water. Beat as directed.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes until tests done with a toothpick.
Let stand for 5 minutes for topping to begin to set.
Turn upside down onto a large platter or a cookie sheet.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Combine pudding mix and syrup in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until it boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Fold in sour cream, coconut, rum and coconut extract.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole. Bake at 350° until heated through and slightly brown on top, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In saucepan, combine all sauce ingredients.
Heat to boiling; simmer 15 minutes.
Arrange chicken in baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Put sauce on chicken and cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: cornbread sausage stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, cook mushrooms, celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add water and bouillon; cook until bouillon dissolves.
In a large bowl, combine mushroom mixture and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Loosely stuff turkey just before roasting, if desired.
Place remaining stuffing in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine sugar, oil and buttermilk; stir into yeast mixture.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead 1 to 2 minutes, or until smooth and elastic.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a floured 2 1/2-cup biscuit cutter.
Place rolls on heavily greased baking sheets; cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Easy and delicious!!

title: corned beef loaf salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill in loaf pan or mold.
Garnish with pickle, peaches, grapes, cold asparagus or sliced tomatoes and cucumbers.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until congealed.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Early in the day or up to 1 month before serving: In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat pie filling and ice cream until smooth and well mixed.
Spoon into crust and freeze one hour.

title: popovers
directions: In a bowl, put flour, salt, eggs and milk .
Beat about 15 seconds with a fork.
Thoroughly grease muffin pan.
Fill cups half full.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together,
except
salmon.
Then marinate the fish for 1 hour.
Bake the fish in the sauce in a 12-inch Dutch oven for 30 minutes.

title: sausage snacks
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Make into balls the size of a small walnut.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until edges are brown.
Serve hot.

title: sweet biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients but mandarin juice and sugar cubes.
Place biscuits on greased cookie sheet.
Cover sugar cube halves with mandarin juice.
When juice is absorbed, gently press one piece of sugar cube into center of each biscuit.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with Sweet Mandarin Butter or Mandarin Marmalade.

title: holiday pull-apart loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine 2 cups flour, 1/3 cup sugar, yeast, lemon zest and salt.
Cut 1/4 cup butter into pieces.
Heat with water and milk until warm (105° to 115°).
Stir into dry ingredients; stir in eggs and flour to make a soft dough.
Knead for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.

title: railroad pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain well.
Mix rest of ingredients with meat and put in casserole dish.

title: pumpkin ketchup(a trinidad special)
directions: Peel, wash and cut pumpkin in chunks.
In 1/2 cup of water boil pumpkin and onions until soft.
Cool a bit and blend until soft and smooth.
Return to heat; add sugar, celery seasoning and all spices.
Add mustard, salt and food coloring.
Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add vinegar and cook for another 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch to thicken mixture and now pour at once into sterile jars.
Leave one inch headroom for fermentation.

title: chili sauce
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes; add ingredients.
Cook until thickened (most of the day).
Pour in hot jars and seal.

title: waffles and pancakes
directions: Mix together milk, flour and baking powder.
Add margarine, then add egg yolks to mixture.
Beat egg whites along with sugar until fluffy; add to mixture.
Beat 1 minute and it's ready to go.

title: avocado balls
directions: Peel and mash avocado.
Add lemon juice and salt with chopped parsley.
Form into small balls and roll in grated carrots.
Serve on toothpick.

title: fat-free flour tortillas
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add Miracle Whip and water.
Mix well.
Add flour if dough is too sticky and knead about 20 minutes. Shape into ball.
Let rest for 15 minutes.
Divide dough and roll into tortillas.
Cook on hot griddle.
Yields 6 tortillas.

title: weight watchers stew
directions: In a large pot, combine ingredients.
Brown chicken until golden brown.
Do not add water.
Cook on low heat about 1 hour. Good over rice or noodles.

title: marinade for chicken and beef
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Marinate chicken overnight.
Grill over charcoal.
For beef, cut into thin strips and marinate overnight.
Grill over charcoal.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add remaining ingredients, beating in eggs, one at a time.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a tube pan.

title: microwave savory onion chicken
directions: Dip chicken in butter.
Coat with dry soup mix and arrange in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish, skin side up, with thick meaty pieces to the outside edges of dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High 18 to 22 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 10 minutes, until meat is tender.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Combine in a plastic container with tight lid the milk, water, orange juice and sugar.
Cover tightly and shake until smooth. Makes 2 portions (1 3/4 cups).

title: taco dip
directions: Layer 1:
Spread jalapeno bean dip in bottom.

title: easy spanish rice
directions: Cook rice (your choice of white or long grain).
Brown ground beef.
Drain fat and rinse meat with water. Drain off water.
Add chopped onions, beef and picante sauce (your choice of mild, medium or hot sauce) to rice.
Mix together evenly.
May serve with refried beans, tacos, or as a side dish to Mexican or barbecue chicken.

title: cheese jello mold
directions: Melt over low heat the lemon jello, hot water and marshmallows, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and let jell.
Add a top layer of raspberry jello.

title: peach punch
directions: Defrost peaches, then mash peaches in a bowl.
Add sugar and all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale prior to serving.

title: herbed beef roast
directions: Moisten meat surface.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and rub on the roast.
Heat oven to 350°.
Place meat on rack and roast to 140° for rare, 160° for medium on meat thermometer.
Time will vary with weight of roast.
Do not cook to well done.

title: blueberry velvet sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk in glass serving dish. Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes, stirring at 2 minute intervals, then stir in milk.
Serve on pancakes, French toast or ice cream.

title: flaky pie crust and crumbs for pies
directions: Rub together until fine.

title: venison loin roast
directions: Wipe roast clean with damp cloth.
Trim off any strong smelling fat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and place in shallow roasting pan, skin side up.
Cut the salt pork in 1/4-inch slices and lay over top of roast.
Place in moderately slow oven about 325° and roast uncovered for 2 hours.
At end of first hour, add 1/4 cup hot water and onions.
When deer is done, remove crisp salt pork and onions and skim extra fat.
Add remaining 1/4 cup water.
Scrape all browned residue from bottom of pan.
Make pan gravy.
Return onions and serve.

title: cookie sandwiches
directions: Put about 1 to 2 tablespoons of icing on oatmeal cookie and place another cookie on top.
Cover and refrigerate for 1/2 hour, then enjoy!
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes. Use with chicken, ribs, etc.
Refrigerate remaining sauce.

title: chocolate oatmeal drops
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Cook on medium heat in saucepan.
Bring to full boil; boil until mixture starts to thicken, continue, stirring so as not to burn.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter and beat until glossy appearance is almost flat.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls and let cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: pepper steak
directions: Melt oleo in skillet. Mash garlic.
Cut steak in 1/2-inch strips. Sprinkle with paprika and set aside.
While preparing other ingredients, brown the steak and garlic in oleo. When brown, add the pepper and onion. Cook until wilted.
Add tomatoes and broth. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Mix soy sauce, water and cornstarch. Stir into mixture and stir until thickened slightly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with all ingredients and refrigerate.
When firm, roll in chopped nuts.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach and nut conserve
directions: Combine
all ingredients except pecans in heavy preserving kettle;
cook,
stirring
frequently until thick, about 30 minutes.
Add
nuts
and stir in well.
Ladle into hot, sterilized canning jars.
Seal immediately.
Yields 3 pints.

title: salmon crunch pie
directions: Drain and flake salmon, reserving liquid.
Add reserved liquid, sour cream, mayo and seasonings to salmon.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn into pie plate, lined with Whole Wheat Crust.
Sprinkle with crumbs reserved from crust.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until filling is set.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and process for 1 minute in blender. Pour pie mixture into 1-quart microwavable dish.

Microwave 8 to 10 minutes on High, stirring once or twice the first 2 to 3 minutes. When edge is set, reduce power to Medium and cook for an additional 6 to 8 minutes until center is set, rotating as necessary.
Very important, whenever you are cooking a pie, cake or quiche, it is necessary for best results to place on shelf up from oven floor, such as a saucer with the pie setting on top of it.

title: refrigerator sweet pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cucumbers.
Pour mixture over pickles.
Put in refrigerator at once.
Should last for 3 to 4 months.

title: shrimp and okra gumbo
directions: Fry fresh okra in 2 tablespoons of oil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly so as not to burn.
Use an aluminum Dutch oven, not a black iron pot.
Remove okra and set aside.
Add margarine and flour.
Make a roux in the same pot.
Chop all vegetables.
Add them and the okra.
Cook for 5 minutes until wilted.
Add 3 quarts of water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook 1 to 2 hours.
Then add shrimp and cook 30 minutes or until tender, seasoning to taste with Creole seasoning.
Serve with boiled rice in a soup plate and garnish with onion tops and sprinkling of file.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and 2 tablespoons sugar in saucepan. Blend in 2 cups milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour remaining milk over bread cubes in a bowl to moisten, then stir into pudding mixture.
Add 1 cup sugar and pineapple; mix well.
Pour in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or bake until firm and lightly browned. Serve warm or chilled.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Clean the mushrooms.
Make sure they are dry and then quarter them.
In a large skillet, melt the butter and saute the mushrooms, onions and celery leaves until golden.
In a blender or food processor, combine 1/2 the mushroom mixture, 1/2 cup cream, 1/2 cup chicken broth and 1/2 the seasonings.
Mix at high speed for 30 seconds or until well blended.
Repeat procedure for second portion.
Reheat without boiling before serving.
Pour into individual bowls and garnish with sour cream and chives.
Serves 8.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: In a bowl, combine the eggs and tomato juice.
Stir in the bread crumbs, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add ground beef and mix well.
On foil or waxed paper, pat meat to a 10 x 8-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices atop meat, leaving a small margin around edges.
Reserve 1 slice of cheese.
Tear up remaining cheese and sprinkle over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat, using foil or waxed paper to lift.
Seal edges and ends.
Place roll, seam side down, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 1/4 hours.
Cut reserved cheese slice into 4 triangles; overlap on top of meat roll. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: english lemon cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in double boiler stirring frequently until thick.
Serve in tart shells or as a filling for layer cakes, or as a spread on toast, biscuits or bread.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Boil 8 to 10 potatoes in skin, let cool.
Slice or chunk potatoes into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sour cream, cream of chicken soup, melted margarine, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese.
Spread over potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded cheese and bake for 15 minutes.
(Cream of mushroom soup can be substituted.)

title: diced tomato salad
directions: Combine lemon juice, cayenne, salt and sugar in a small bowl. Add tomatoes and toss together gently, but thoroughly.
Let salad marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes before serving.

title: tang pie
directions: Hand mixed. Mix softened cream cheese until creamy. Add Eagle Brand milk slowly while mixing. Add sour cream and mix thoroughly. Add Tang and mix until completely dissolved. Mixture will be pale orange. Add lemon juice and mix until it is completely blended in with the mixture. Pour into pie shell and refrigerate for at least 6 hours. Preferably overnight so pies can set up well.

title: lemon custards
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly oil 4 (6-ounce) custard cups or spray with a nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except maple syrup.
Beat with a fork or a wire whisk for several minutes until well blended.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving pieces. Pound flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt into steak. Brown in fry pan on both sides. Place in dutch oven. Add hot water to meat drippings in pan. Add a little flour, bring to boil and pour over meat. This should be thin as it thickens while baking. Bake in a slow oven (300°) for about 3 hours. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: oven omelet
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 12 or 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Tilt the pan so the sides get coated.
Combine eggs, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Stir in onions, parsley and pepper.
Add 1 cup grated cheese.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese (grated).
Bake at 325° until set, about 35 minutes. Note:
Ham, bacon or sausage may be added.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: peanut butter meltaway fudge
directions: In 4 qt. saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk, butter, corn syrup, and vinegar. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full rolling boil. Boil and stir 5 minutes.

title: mock oyster dip
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add drained mushrooms, mushroom soup, cheese and cooked broccoli that has been drained of juice.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Season to taste.
Use as dip or in patty shells.

title: prissy's cake that doesn't last
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add pineapple (drained).
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well but do not beat. Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: orange salad
directions: Pour boiling water slowly over gelatin and pudding and stir well.
Add pineapple, oranges and Cool Whip.
Fold gently and place in refrigerator to set.

title: smokies
directions: Put smokies in crock-pot.
Pour in barbecue sauce.
Simmer about 2 hours.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with a little milk.
Mix in the dry taco seasoning; add sour cream.
Spread on a cookie sheet.
Top with lettuce, tomato, onion, cheese and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and mix one egg at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: new broccoli casserole
directions: Defrost frozen broccoli.
Layer broccoli in dish.
Mix the soup, 2 eggs and Ranch dressing; pour over broccoli.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to 35 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook and drain noodles; brown and drain ground beef.
Combine noodles, beef, sauce, soup, tomato sauce, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Pour layer of mixture in dish; layer with cheese, alternating sauce, then cheese with sauce on top layer.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: herb bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread evenly on bread.
Bake at 350°, open-faced, until melted and slightly browned.
May also broil slightly at the end.
Excellent side dish with pasta.

title: melt-in-your-mouth blueberry cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together onto a sheet of waxed paper; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.

title: minted coffee mix
directions: Combine ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until blended.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
1 cup mix.

title: wedding punch
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and 9 cups of water.
Dissolve Jell-O in 6 cups of hot water.
Add sugar mixture to Jell-O.
Add pure apple juice, lemon juice and almond extract.
When ready to serve, add the ginger ale.
Serves 100 people.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix to form a stiff dough.
Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness. Cut with cookie cutters.
make hole for ribbon.
Carefully place on rack to dry.
Let air dry several days, turning occasionally. Makes 12 ornaments.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking powder.
Add pumpkin, oil, eggs, nuts and raisins.
Stir until moistened and smooth.
Pour into pans.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until done.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Melt 2 to 3 tablespoons butter in large skillet and add garlic. Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper. Put in skillet; brown over low to medium heat, cooking slowly. Turn chicken once; add mushrooms and onions. Continue to cook slowly until done. While chicken is cooking, prepare the sauce.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup, milk, Parmesan cheese, onion and sour cream.
Stir in turkey and zucchini.
Add spaghetti; toss gently to coat.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish or casserole. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with additional Parmesan cheese if desired.
Serves 4.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine all ingredients (except ginger ale). The ginger ale should be added just prior to serving. If more color is desired, add a few drops of food coloring. This mixture may be made ahead of time and frozen. Serves 35 to 40.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream margarine,
Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat.
Add buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients. Mix well. Stir
in
lemon
and
almond
extracts.
Pour
into greased and floured Bundt pan.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Turn out on wire rack and cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil until color of light brown.
Take off heat and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Stir once and pour into cookie sheet.

title: quick dip
directions: Heat cream cheese until soft (about 15 seconds in microwave). Add hot sauce over cream cheese.
Serve with chips.
You can use any hot sauce, mild or hot.
Doesn't matter.
It is much better than it sounds!

title: nonfat fudge sauce
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Stir in evaporated skim milk.
Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until thick.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more after sauce starts to bubble.
Remove from
heat and stir in vanilla.
Makes 1 cup.
One tablespoon equals 47 calories and 0 fat.

title: baked peach pancake
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon brown sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice. Add peach slices, tossing to coat. Set aside. Whisk together remaining 2 tablespoons brown sugar, milk, eggs and flour. Set mixture aside. Heat butter in a 9-inch ovenproof skillet at 425° for 5 minutes or until butter melts. Pour batter into hot skillet. Spoon peach mixture over batter. Bake pancake at 425° for 16 to 18 minutes or until puffed and golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with maple syrup. Yield: 4 servings.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Coat chicken breasts with flour and dip in eggs.
Coat with combined bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Brown chicken on all sides in hot oil.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Saute onions in remaining oil in skillet and stir in remaining ingredients except Swiss cheese.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with Swiss cheese and continue baking until cheese is melted.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of muffin cups. Beat egg slightly with fork.
Stir in milk, pumpkin and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fold in raisins.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon sugar over each muffin.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream cheese with butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in flour cup by cup (dough should be soft).
Roll into small balls, about the size of a nickel.
Press on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top with pecan half.
Bake for 12 minutes at 375°.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In large bowl, mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in hot water and butter.
Mix in only enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
On floured surface, knead 4 minutes.
On greased baking sheet, roll dough to 14 x 10-inches, spreading dressing down center third of dough length. Top with layers of beef or ham, cheese and sauerkraut.
Make cuts from filling to dough edges at 1-inch intervals along sides of fillings.
Alternate sides, fold strips at an angle across filling. Cover.
Place large shallow pan on counter half filled with boiling water.
Place baking sheet over pan on counter.
Let rise for 15 minutes.
Brush with egg whites.
Sprinkle with seeds.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: crisp molasses cookies
directions: Mix shortening, molasses and sugar until smooth.
Stir in sour milk, then sifted dry ingredients; add lemon extract.
Mix to a smooth, stiff dough and chill until firm.
Roll out a portion of dough on floured surface to a thickness of 1/8-inch.
Cut with floured cutter; place on greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or shape into 9-inch rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper or clear plastic wrap.
Chill well.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices and bake at 350° until brown.

title: tuna rice dinner(20 minutes)
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add onion, cook and stir until tender, but not browned.
Stir in tuna, Minute rice and parsley.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish with almonds, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. Recipes can be doubled.

title: ding bats
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs and dates.
Cook together over low heat until dissolved.
Add pecans and cook 10 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and stir. Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Form in small balls and roll in coconut.

title: vanilla ice cream(club member: nicholas thompson)
directions: Beat eggs. Gradually add sugar; beat. Add condensed milk and vanilla flavoring. Pour into 1 gallon freezer. Fill remaining with whole milk.

title: cherry rhubarb jam
directions: Combine ingredients except for gelatin and bring to a boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir well until dissolved.
Put into jars or other container.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Melt cheese.
Add Bisquick and sausage and stir together. Roll into balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Insert toothpicks.

title: purple passion salad
directions: Soften cream cheese with mixer.
Mix enough cherry and pineapple juice to make 1/2 cup.
Add juice to the cream cheese and blend well.
Add the other ingredients to the cheese mixture and blend.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate for at least one hour.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: party mix
directions: Mix and cook at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place ingredients except parsley and Bugles in blender and puree.
Pour into serving bowl and chill.
Garnish with parsley. Serve with Bugles.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: crepes
directions: In a bowl combine flour, milk, eggs and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat with a rotary beater until blended.
Lightly oil an 8-inch skillet; heat over medium heat.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter into skillet; immediately rotate pan until batter covers the bottom.
Cook until lightly browned, turn and brown on other side.
Repeat until all batter is used.
If desired, while warm, spread applesauce, sweetened strawberries, jelly or jam thinly on crepes; roll up.
Yield:
About 12 crepes.

title: good granola
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Add honey, oil and vanilla and mix well.
Spread on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on paper towels.
Eat for a snack or breakfast.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake in well-greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack in pans for 10 minutes; then turn out of pans to cool on rack.
Makes 2 regular loaf size or 6 mini-loaf size.

title: crab fettucine
directions: Saute garlic in butter; blend in crab, cream, cheese and pepper.
Cook and stir until thoroughly heated.
Add hot noodles; toss lightly.
Salt to taste.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Melt butter; mix with crumbs and sugar.
Line 10 x 14 x 2-inch pan with half of mixture (save other half for top).
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sugar; cool.
Beat in cream cheese and vanilla.
Whip evaporated milk until very stiff and add slowly to Jell-O mixture.
Pour over crumbs in pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top of Jell-O mixture and chill at least 3 hours.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together; drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
May be iced with confectioners sugar glaze, if desired.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Sprinkle with paprika and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: doris' toffee chocolate squares
directions: Line
a
x 15-inch pan with graham crackers, cut to fit (not crumbs).
Simmer sugar and butter 3 minutes and stir well until very well mixed.
Pour over crackers evenly.
Bake at
400° for 5 minutes (until bubbling).
Sprinkle with chocolate
chips to
cover.
Spread with knife as chocolate melts. Sprinkle with nuts while chocolate is still soft.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Roll meat, soup mix, egg and cracker crumbs into small balls and brown to thoroughly cook meat. Combine Coke and catsup to make sauce.
Place browned meatballs in sauce and cook for 30 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all together with hand.
Chill overnight.
Roll in ball. Roll in pecans.

title: gumdrop  cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Blend. Add oats, coconut, gumdrop pieces and vanilla.
Mix with spoon until well blended.
Roll dough into small balls; place on greased cookie sheet.
Press each ball with a fork.
Bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
They improve in flavor if stored for a few days.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes for loaf pan or 1 hour for flat pan.
Remove from oven and immediately drain all the grease off.
Put on serving platter and garnish with catsup.
Serves 8.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Whip the cream. Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Pour in mold and freeze. Slice to serve.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Bring 5 quarts of water to a rolling boil.
Add tortellini and cook until plump and tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Trim fat from Prosciutto and cut into small squares.
Steam peas until just tender, then plunge into cold water to stop cooking and preserve color.
Pick over basil, removing all stems.
Wash and let dry on a paper towel.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Combine sugar, milk and Karo in heavy saucepan.
Bring to rolling boil and boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and place in pan of cold water.
Add margarine, peanut butter and vanilla, beat until it thickens to spreading consistency.
(Don't give up, sometimes it takes a little while to thicken.)
If it gets too thick, add a little milk.

title: rice and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add uncooked noodles, stirring constantly, until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn noodle-rice mixture into 3-quart casserole dish.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Put into oven. Bake 45 minutes.

title: old fashion buck wheat cakes
directions: Mix together the buck wheat flour, plain flour, water, yeast and salt the night before and let them stand overnight.
Next morning, add butter, soda and molasses.
Stir up good and bake on hot griddle.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all juices together and mix 1/2 of juice with 3 tablespoons Tang and add to fruit.

title: gerald's favorite brisket(mayor gilkey's favorite)
directions: At least 8 hours before cooking, place brisket in baking dish and pour liquid smoke over meat.
Generously sprinkle each side of brisket with celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 8 hours, but can be refrigerated up to 5 days. Allow at least 5 hours for baking.
When ready to bake, sprinkle both sides of brisket with small amount of Worcestershire sauce. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, covered, in a 275° oven 5 hours or in a 175° oven for 8 to 10 hours.
Cool and slice.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Reheat before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Crush the Thai peppers until fully crushed.
Place in a large bowl.
Shred cucumbers and carrots and place in bowl with peppers. Toss until fully mixed.
Cut cherry tomatoes in half.
Gently squeeze the juice from the tomatoes into the mixed vegetables and then drop tomatoes in.
Add salt and lime juice into the mixed vegetables and toss salad again.

title: orange beets
directions: Cook beets in water approximately 35 to 45 minutes or until tender, covered. Run under cold water. Slip off skins and remove any root ends.
Mix brown sugar, cornstarch, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper in a 2-quart saucepan. Stir orange juice gradually into cornstarch mixture. Stir in vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in beets.
Heat until hot.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Mix well.
May omit some or all of the sugar or replace it with artificial sweetener.

title: peanut brittle pie
directions: Remove peanut brittle bag from box and put a couple of small holes in it, then wrap it in a kitchen towel and with a butcher knife handle, pound candy until it is in very small pieces, turning bag. Dump Cool Whip and candy pieces in a large bowl and mix well. Put this mixture into your pie crust and cover with plastic lid that came with the crust. Let chill at least 24 hours before serving. Serve topped with whipped cream. Yum, yum.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix shortening with next 3 ingredients.
Sift flour and salt and stir in shortening mixture.
Roll dough in 1-inch balls.
Beat egg white.
Dip balls into white.
Roll in pecans.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; press thumb in top of each cookie.
Put decorations in thumbprint.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: chili(yield: 6-8 servings)
directions: 1. Brown meat, drain off fat.

title: frozen peach pie
directions: Mix milk with lemon juice. Mixture will become thick. Fold in whipped topping, peaches and vanilla. Pour into crust. Freeze until firm. Cut with knife dipped in hot water. Serve frozen. Serves 8.

title: scallop corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt Crisco in a large heavy skillet. Stir in carrots, green pepper, celery and onion.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are barely tender.
Stir in corn, eggs, cracker crumbs, evaporated milk, Tabasco sauce, sugar and salt. Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is set and top is golden.
Remove from oven.
Garnish with parsley and olives.

title: easy mexican chicken
directions: Skin the chicken.
Place in plastic bag with taco mix and shake until well coated.
Place in baking pan and bake at 375° for 30 - 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: frozen pops
directions: Dissolve jello, Kool-Aid and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Mix well.
Pour into ice cube trays, small paper cups or frozen pop molds.
Insert wooden sticks or plastic spoons diagonally in each ice cube section or at an angle in molds or cups for handle.
If desired, pops may be partially frozen before handles are inserted.
Freeze until firm, 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 20 to 24 pops.

title: page's punch
directions: For 1 gallon have ready 2 (1/2 gallon) containers.
Makeup lemonade as directed on can.
Put one quart in each container. Add 2 cups white grape juice to each container.

Refrigerate. Just before serving, add cold ginger ale to fill each container. Ice cubes can be made of ginger ale, or lemonade, or punch mixture. Add tiny wedge of lemon and 1/2 a cherry for color to each.

title: honey dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Process for 30 seconds or until creamy.
May be stored in refrigerator indefinitely.
Makes 4 cups.

title: chicken broccoli braid
directions: Add first 5 ingredients with mayonnaise. Add garlic salt, dried dill weed and slivered almonds. To form crust, unroll the crescent rolls (do not separate triangles) onto a cookie sheet or rectangular baking stone. Smooth until all perforations are sealed. On the long side of crust, slit the dough 3-inches deep every 1 1/2-inches. Pour the chicken filling down the center of the crust. To braid, lift strips of dough across mixture to meet in center, twisting each strip one turn together. Continue down the length of the dough. Pinch ends of roll together. Using a pastry brush, brush on egg white. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375° until golden brown. Enjoy.

title: holiday yam bake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice. Add juice to yams, sugar and butter.
Beat well. Stir in pineapple and pecans.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole. Spoon in mixture. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with marshmallows. Bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: royal hot chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate in large, heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk.
Gradually add water, stirring until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Garnish with whipped cream and cinnamon if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables and drain.
Heat together can of mushroom soup and milk.
Add tuna, drained and flaked, cheese, hot rice and vegetables.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with more grated cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: no name fudge recipe
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt together in a saucepan. Heat to boiling at medium heat. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add the marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts. Stir 1 to 2 minutes until the marshmallows are melted. Pour into a buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan. Cool, then cut into squares!

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and onion; cook according to package directions.
Drain and add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix
oleo
and	graham crackers.
Spread on bottom of a large dish.
Beat
eggs,	softened oleo and sugar for 15 minutes. Spread over graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas on top of	this mixture.
Drain
pineapple	and spread over bananas. Cover	with Cool
Whip.
Sprinkle
with
cherries
and	nuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a bowl; mix last 3 ingredients in a saucepan and heat until it boils.
Let it boil for 60 seconds. Drop butter in the pan and remove from the heat.
Dump contents of saucepan into bowl which contains first 3 ingredients.
Mix.
Set teaspoon-sized scoops of mix on sheet or aluminum foil and let set until cool.
Eat.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb; while hot, stir in sugar and jello.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: hot fudge pudding cake(the holt's)
directions: *One-half cup granulated sugar can be used for 1/2 cup light brown sugar.
The taste and texture will change a little; both are good!!

title: mexican salad
directions: Saute until well done (meat and spices).
Melt Velveeta and Ro-Tel.
Serve layered with corn chips, meat mixture, cheese and Ro-Tel.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Bring water to boil, add dash of celery salt.
Boil chicken breasts until cooked.
Tear chicken into pieces.
Mix soups, yogurt and chicken.
Place in casserole dish and top with crackers, oleo and poppy seed.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix in saucepan 3/4 cup sugar, flour, salt and cornstarch. Add water and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Beat until thick the egg yolks, 1/4 cup sugar and small amount of hot mixture to eggs. Then stir eggs into hot mixture.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter and cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice and pour into cooked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in sheet cake pan following the directions on the box.
Crumble half of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Pour half of pudding on crumbled cake. Slice two bananas on top of pudding. Layer half a can of pineapple, half the pie filling and half the whipped topping on top of the bananas.
Repeat layering, finishing with whipped topping.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix turkey, salad oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt.
Let stand overnight.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes by scalding in boiling water for 1 minute and then putting in cold water.
Cook tomatoes in 6-quart pot.
Add peppers and onions.
Simmer to cook down for about 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and boil for 30 minutes.
Prepare pint jars and canning lids as per manufacturer's instructions.
Place chili sauce in jars and seal.
Yields 6 to 7 pints.

title: real texas chili(no heartburn)
directions: In a 4-quart pot, cook beef until it changes color, but does not brown.
Lower heat.
Stir in garlic.
Combine chili powder, cumin and flour.
Sprinkle over meat.
Add 1 1/2 cans beef broth. Stir.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer about 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add remaining broth and cook 15 minutes more.
Add the refried beans and chili beans.
If too thick, add a little water and cook 15 minutes more.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco; add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until tested done, "Do not open oven for at least 1 hour."
Cake will most likely fall if you do.

title: macaroni and cheese(with a twist!)
directions: Cook and stir ham, pepper and onion in hot margarine in large skillet over medium-high heat until vegetables are tender.
Stir in Cheddar cheese sauce.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add pasta and toss to coat.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: delightful fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine sugar, flour, egg and pineapple juice in a small saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Cool.
Combine pecans and fruit.
Add dressing, stirring well. Chill before serving.

title: potato dumplings
directions: In bowl, combine ingredients.
With floured fingers, form potato mixture into ten 2-inch balls.
Dust lightly with flour before dropping into hot bubbling stew.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray a casserole pan with Pam.
Put layer of potatoes in pan, then layer of cheese.
Sprinkle onion flakes over the cheese. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Prepare the second layer the same as first layer.
Pour whipping cream over the potatoes.
Cook at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water following package directions.
Drain well.
Toss hot, drained macaroni with Italian or French dressing and cool.
Add remaining ingredients to macaroni.
Mix lightly.
Chill in refrigerator until serving time. Serve on crisp lettuce.
(Arrange on platter with assortment of sliced meats and cheese.)

title: summer taco salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and picante sauce with mixer.
Pour into dish.
Add some Cheddar cheese.
Top with lettuce, chopped tomatoes, chopped black olives and last of all, more Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve as dip for corn chips.

title: my favorite butter cake
directions: Cream sugar and soft butter together in large bowl.
Add beaten eggs and beat on low speed with mixer.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Blend in alternately with milk.
Mix together by hand until flour is all folded in, then beat with mixer for 3 or 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat 1 more minute.
Bake at 350° in a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for about an hour or until light golden brown and top springs back when lightly touched.
No frosting is necessary as this is so good, but if you insist, just use a light vanilla or lemon glaze.
Keeps very well.

title: hawaiian delight ice cream
directions: Mix together and put into ice cream freezer.
Using crushed ice in your freezer will result in smoother, less grainy ice cream.
Layer crushed ice and salt.
Follow directions that come with freezer as to proportion of salt to ice.
If you have a small freezer container, you may want to half the recipe...this makes a big batch of ice cream.

title: deep dish apple dumplings
directions: Melt 3/4 stick of Parkay margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Distribute to cover bottom and coat sides.
Add apples, spreading evenly.
Combine brown sugar, flour and spice.
Sprinkle liberally over apples.
Put in 375° oven and cook 45 minutes, stirring a couple of times.
Okay if juicy.
Carefully remove from oven and top with flaky biscuits pulled apart into halves.
Top biscuits with 1/4 stick of margarine (a dab to each) and you may sprinkle top with brown sugar or spice very lightly.

title: pecan cheese wafers
directions: Combine cheese and butter; mix well.
Add flour, salt and pepper to creamed mixture.
Stir in cereal last.
Chill 2 hours. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli in buttered casserole.
Mix soup, mushrooms, cheese, onion and garlic powder over broccoli.
Make stuffing. Place on top.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake until crisp and brown at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter and cream with sugar.
Beat well after adding each egg.
Add a little milk and coconut.
Add the rest of milk and extract.
Pour in uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until done.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Rub chops with salt and pepper; melt butter in skillet.
Add chops, brown lightly on both sides.
Remove chops, add onions. Brown lightly.
Put sliced potatoes in baking dish.
Arrange chops over top.
Add soup and milk to onions in skillet.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes, uncover and bake additional 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cut 12 donuts and hole from bread and set aside.
Cut off crusts.
Tear remaining bread into bite size pieces.
Spread across bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place layer of cheese over bread, then layer of broccoli and a layer of ham.
Arrange donuts and holes on top.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread and all.
Cover and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight. Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cheese bubbles. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: whipped pineapple jello
directions: Put boiling water in bowl.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Stir in ice cubes and mix until melted.
Remove 1 cup Jell-O and put in a medium bowl.
Put remaining Jell-O in a serving bowl and let it set.
When the one cup of Jell-O is almost set, mix in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip and 1 small can crushed pineapple (drained).
When mixed, spoon over set Jell-O.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: dilled broccoli salad(diabetic recipe)
directions: Wash broccoli; cut into small florets.
Mix all ingredients together; put in a sealed plastic bowl.
Chill overnight.
Every once in a while, shake the bowl so everything stays mixed together and evenly coated.
Serve cold as either finger or fork food.

title: salmon platter salad(serves 4)
directions: Marinate green beans in dressing for at least 1 hour; drain and reserve marinade.
Remove skin and bones from salmon and break into large chunks.
Place salmon and green beans on platter lined with salad greens.
Garnish with tomatoes and cucumber.
Combine reserved marinade with sour cream and serve with salad.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Beat together sour cream, eggs, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles and drain.
Butter 2-quart casserole or pan.
Place one layer of cooked noodles, one layer of ham and then pour a little of egg mixture and a few pieces of butter.
Repeat ending with ham on top.
Place the rest of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach preserves
directions: Wash and peel peaches.
Cut in half.
Remove and discard pits. Cut into small pieces in a large kettle.
Add sugar and bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 10 minutes or until as tender as desired.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal immediately.

title: american chop suey
directions: Put uncooked rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Brown meat until it turns color.
Pour off any grease.
To meat, add celery, onion, soy sauce, soup and water.
Pour over rice and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Do not stir.
Just before serving, heat bean sprouts; drain liquid and spread on casserole.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: easy butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons of warm water.
Combine sugar, shortening, 1 cup of warm water, salt and eggs in a large bowl. Mix well.
Add yeast and flour; beat until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough into circle; brush with melted butter.
Cut 16 triangles.
Roll triangles up, beginning with wide end.
Place on greased baking sheet point sides down.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in a casserole dish.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in large casserole.
DO NOT PRE COOK macaroni.
Bake at 300°
for 1 hour. Best if you can mix the night before cooking the next day and be sure and keep refrigerated.

title: almond breakfast cake
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and add flour, salt and almond extract.
Mix well.
Line a 10-inch skillet with foil and pour batter over it.
Top the batter with slivered almonds and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil after cake has cooled.
Serves 8.

title: ole-time chocolate cake
directions: Beat sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Add salt, flour, baking soda, water and cocoa.
Pour into pans.
Bake 30 minutes or until done.

title: communion wine
directions: Crush berries.
Place in a large stoneware crock.
Cook with boiling water.
Cover with lid on crock.
Let set for 3 days.
At end of the 3rd day, strain the juice and discard the pulp.
Add sugar to juice.
Stir to mix well.
Place juice in an air-locked container for 3 months (5 gallon glass carkoy).
Bottle the wine and place in your wine cellar or have a cheese and wine party for 50 friends.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Sprinkle in crumbs and press in pan.
Add each ingredient in order, making layers.
Drizzle milk evenly over layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix together and store in tight-fitting container. To serve, use 2 heaping teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: baked onions
directions: Heat honey, butter and salt in a saucepan (or microwave cup) until the butter just melts.
Slice onions but do not separate rings.
Arrange slices in greased baking pan.
Pour honey
mixture evenly over onions.
Bake for 45 minutes at 450° or until golden brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef in butter.
Transfer to a pot.
Saute onions; add to meat.
Also add remaining ingredients; cook over medium-low heat, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: creamed corn
directions: Fry fatback.
Let grease cool after taking meat out.
Pour corn in pan.
Pour in 1/4 cup water.
Mix flour and water together. Pour flour mix into pan.
Cook on high until it boils.
Heat and cook 5 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Salt and pepper.

title: snack crackers
directions: Put all except oil in paper bag.
Shake.
Pour oil into bag over crackers.
Shake and let stand 24 hours.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Soak dates in hot water, mixed with soda, until most of water is absorbed.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add date mixture and mix well.
Add mayonnaise, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: brigadeirao
directions: Blend all together in a blender.
Pour it in a mold, greased with no-stick corn oil and sprinkled with sugar.
Bake it in the oven for about 40 minutes at 350°.
Test it with a toothpick until it comes out dry.
Let it cool and unmold.
Sprinkle top with granulated choco-mint.

title: elegant potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; cook, peel and shred on medium grater.
Shred cheese on same grater; do not wash in between uses. Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Alternate layers of potatoes and cheese.
Sprinkle salt on each layer.
Pour whipped cream over potato-cheese mix.
Top with bread crumbs and butter mixture and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: crock-pot beef
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir together.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 12 hours (or high for 4 to 6 hours).
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: texas tortillas
directions: Place all ingredients except tortillas and picante sauce in a food processor.
Process until smooth. Spread mixture on flour tortillas and roll up.
Place in damp paper towels and place in Ziploc storage bags. Chill.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Add sour cream, Cool Whip, salt and vanilla.
Layer with bananas and vanilla wafers.
Top with crumbled vanilla wafers.
Chill and it's ready to eat.

title: green beans(canned)
directions: Snap and wash green beans.
Fill quart jars, then add 1 teaspoon of salt per quart jar.
Fill with water to the neck of the jar.
Put 1 1/2-quarts of water in canner and pressure for 15 minutes at 10 pounds of pressure.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, add lemon juice, Worcestershire, garlic powder, salt and pepper to cream cheese. Blend well.
Fold in crabmeat and spoon mixture into small baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve with Pepperidge Farm crackers.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into glass bowl.
Let stand at least 12 hours before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Add zucchini, sifted flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well. Add nuts. Bake in two loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit, raisins and pecans in a large pan.
Pour sugar over fruit and mix with hands until fruit is coated with sugar.
Pour flour over fruit/sugar and mix with hands.
Beat eggs and pour over mixture; mix well.
Pour melted butter over all and mix well.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and rinse spaghetti in boiling water; drain.
Add all ingredients and refrigerate until serving.

title: onion patties
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients.
Add enough milk to make a thick batter.
Mix in onions.
Fry in deep fat or in smaller amount of fat, if desired.

title: homemade pecan pie
directions: Beat together the ingredients.
Add 1 cup pecans and stir with spoon.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes or until set at 350°.
Serve cold.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Put milk in bowl.
Add egg yolks.
Gradually add lemon juice, beating until thick.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites; add to pie for topping.

title: orange jello
directions: Mix Jell-O, Cool Whip and cream cheese (whipped cream cheese is easier).
Then add pineapple, oranges and fruit cocktail.

title: "that good dessert"
directions: Mix together; grease your hand and press into 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: white chili
directions: Saute onions, garlic and chili pepper in a heavy saucepan. Add chili powder, cumin, broth and turkey; simmer 1 hour.
Add cooked or canned beans and simmer 15 minutes.
Add shredded cheese until melted and blended.
Add sour cream just before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease baking dish; put in brown sugar; add the pineapple on top.
Put the dry cake mix over top;
then slice butter and cover the
mix.
Then
sprinkle
the chopped nuts on top. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve 2 packages gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cold water and the vinegar.
Chill until thickened.
Pour 1/2 cup of gelatin into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Arrange 3 pineapple rings on top.
Fold in banana slices and spoon 1 cup gelatin into pan. Chill again until set, but not firm.
Blend mayonnaise into remaining thickened gelatin until mixture is smooth.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in order; bake at 350° for 1 hour, in 3 (1-pound) coffee cans, greased and floured.
This freezes well for an indefinite period of time.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix zucchini and cheese together.
Mix Bisquick, salt, pepper and oregano together, then mix with first part.
In blender, put eggs, oil, and onion.
Blend and mix with other ingredients. Grease bowl.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or 325° for glass dish.

title: honey peaches
directions: Place drained peach halves in an oblong baking dish.
In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, then add honey to taste. Continue to beat until mixed well.
In each peach half, put a spoonful of the cream cheese-honey mixture.
Bake until hot (about 20 or 25 minutes) in a 350° oven.
Serve hot, in place of a salad. Delicious!!

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Mix butter and sugar, add eggs, and mashed bananas.
Combine flour and soda; slowly blend with sugar mixture.
Add pecans, bake in muffin tin for 20 minutes at 400° or until brown.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in a medium bowl.
Mix in Bisquick and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into a ball on surface dusted with Bisquick.
Knead 10 times.

title: blueberry ring cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs and sour cream.
Fold in blueberries.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Bake and shred chicken. Mix chicken, soups and onion together with Ro-Tel. Crush bag of Doritos and place 1/2 bag in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Pour chicken mixture on top.
Put remaining 1/2 bag of Doritos on top,
then top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix meatball ingredients together.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll the balls into flour and brown in fry pan.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Cut into bite-size pieces. Mix chicken with cream of chicken soup, sour cream, chicken broth and butter (melted).
Top with Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: honey milk balls
directions: Combine honey and peanut butter.
Add nonfat dry milk and oats, a little at a time. Shape into small balls and place on waxed paper or a plate.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Then add potatoes and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: alabama chocolate-pecan jumbo christmas fudge pie
directions: Combine wafers and 1/3 cup melted butter for crust or use 2 ready made chocolate crusts.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples. Prepare dough of flour, salt, milk, baking powder and Crisco. Work out and divide into 6 equal balls of dough. Flour board and roll out placing one whole apple in center of dough. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon into hole of apple, then wrap and sit into baking dish.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Gradually add strawberries. Process until smooth and slightly thickened.
Yields 3 3/4 cups.

title: darlene's sex in a pan(i.e. sex pie)
directions: Blend powdered sugar, cream cheese and half of the Cool Whip. Spread over crust. Combine instant pudding, milk and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes. Spread over cream cheese mixture. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding and garnish with remaining pecans.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook meat on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Keep adding water so you don't boil the meat dry.
Meat should be tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for several hours.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Stir; bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add oats and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Drop onto wax paper.
Harden and serve.

title: 4-h cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon.
Butter bottom of flat glass once.
Dip in sugar and press mound of dough.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: golden chicken stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to package directions and place stuffing in baking dish.
Wash chicken breasts and pat dry.
Fillet each chicken breast into two slices.
Place chicken breasts on top of stuffing and press down into stuffing.

title: cinnamon raisin biscuits
directions: Mix and place onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease two 12-inch pizza pans. Cream first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and beat until light.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Divide dough in half and press into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: mom watkins' turkey dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery a few minutes, until tender.
Mix all together.
Add enough stock to make dressing moist.
Put a few pats of butter on top.
Bake at 375° in glass baking dish until brown.

title: super apples
directions: Put apples in baking dish.
If using fresh apples, cover with the water and lemon juice.
If using canned apples, omit water and lemon juice.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread over apples.
Cover dish.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: renee's chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in micro 10 to 15 minutes. Let cool. Brown celery and onions in oil. Add all ingredients (except pasta) and cook on low heat. Stir often until oleo and cheese melt. Cook pasta and drain. Add to sauce and toss. Cook in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine first four ingredients and beat well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: coconut leche flan(caramel flan)
directions: Caramel sugar with 1/4 cup water.
Line a suitable mold with 3/4 of the caramelized syrup evenly and set aside.
Stir the milk into the remaining 1/4 of the caramelized syrup.
Place over low heat and stir continuously until all caramel is dissolved.
Mix egg yolk and slightly beaten whites and beat lightly to mix thoroughly. Add sugar and lemon rind; then add coconut milk with caramelized syrup.
Mix well.
Strain through a cheesecloth and pour into mold previously lined with caramel.
Cook slowly in a pan with hot water without allowing the water to boil.

After about 1 1/2 hours of cooking, place a piece of plain metal sheet over the mold and over this place a few pieces of live charcoal to brown top of custard. Or slip under broiler in oven just long enough to brown.

title: rolled chicken supremes
directions: Prepare Supremes by wrapping cheese and then ham around each breast.
Secure well with wooden toothpicks.
Beat eggs; dip each Supreme in egg and roll in breadcrumbs.
In shallow baking dish, melt 1 stick of butter and add Supremes.
Place on low rack in 350° oven and bake 35 minutes, turning only once during cooking time.
Baste often, adding more butter if necessary.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and remove stems from mushrooms.
In blender, blend 1 slice bread (in pieces) and spices.
Add remaining bread in pieces and stems a little at a time.
Melt butter in pan.
Add mixture and saute for 5 minutes.
Stuff caps.
Set caps in shallow well-greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 20 minutes.

title: margaret's coconut cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in 2 whole eggs and two egg yolks.
Stir in vanilla and sift flour, salt and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture, along with milk.
Bake in 3 layers until done.
Cool.

title: texas baked beans
directions: Mix all.
Crumble bacon over top and mix slightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: reese's peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter, milk and cream cheese in a large bowl. Beat well on low speed.
Add the confectioners sugar and 1 c. of the cool whip.
Mix until creamy and smooth.
Pour 1/3 of the mixture into the graham cracker crust.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup and sprinkle with Reese cup chunks.
Repeat layers 2 more times.
Top with additional cool whip and drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Sprinkle with Reese cup chunks.
Freeze until firm.
Serve slightly thawed.
Store leftovers in the freezer.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and mix well.
Shape dough around unwrapped chocolate kiss. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: lisa's fudge
directions: Mix together in a big bowl the Hershey bars, chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling. Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add to mixture and beat until creamy.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with any hot or cold fish.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes; pat dry.
Prick with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or microwave until done.
Cool until you can handle with hands.
Cut lengthwise into wedges.
Cut center away leaving 1/4 inch.
Prepare topping.
Fry skins in oil until crisp.
Divide topping between skins.
Sprinkle with cream cheese and bacon on top.
Bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Serve immediately.

title: banana bread(no sugar)
directions: Cream eggs, oil and sugar.
Add bananas, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well and put in well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and eggs together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix fruit and nuts in enough flour to coat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Beat with eggbeater the first 5 ingredients; add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Let rise until light in a greased pan or covered dish in refrigerator.
Knead dough and make rolls the size of a walnut; let rise in greased baking pans.
Butter tops and bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Butter tops again to keep rolls soft.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; add berries and mix well.
Pour into pastry-lined pie tin; moisten edge of dough with water. Cover with top crust, making opening for steam to escape.
Press pastry well over edge and trim.
If canned berries are used, measure scant 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.

title: zesty white sauce
directions: Melt over low heat the butter.
Stir slowly with flour until well blended.
Stir in slowly the milk (or milk and light stock, or stock and cream).
Simmer and stir the sauce until it has thickened and is smooth.

title: mustard-balsamic vinegar sauce(for beef, chicken or pork)
directions: In a heavy skillet over medium-high heat, add olive oil and cook meat to desired doneness.
Remove meat and keep warm.
To skillet, add chicken broth, balsamic vinegar and mustard.
Over medium-high heat, heat mixture to boiling, stirring constantly and scraping the bottom of the pan until browned bits are dissolved and mixture reduces slightly.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix together sugar and water and put meat into for 8 hours. Add barbecue sauce, salt and catsup; mix these well.
Place all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish. Cook at 250° for 4 hours or 300° for 3 hours. Be careful at 300° not to burn sauce.

title: spoon bread
directions: Set
oven
at 500° and place a 2-quart casserole, well-greased, in oven.

title: rocky road
directions: In top of double boiler, over hot not boiling water, melt chips with milk.
Remove from heat.
Put in a long bowl with marshmallows, nuts and raisins.
Mix in chocolate and milk.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper lined baking sheet.
Chill 2 hours. Store loosely covered in cool, dry place.
This amount makes 5 dozen.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and 1/4 cup milk in 2-quart saucepan.
Add egg yolks and blend.
Add milk; mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to full boil (about 10 minutes).
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in cooled pudding mixture.
Add vanilla and Grand Marnier; cool 2 hours.
Just before serving, whip the cream and add.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Serves 12.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Parboil vegetables until tender.
Place in casserole with soup and sour cream.
Pour butter over mixture; sprinkle top with croutons.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix together and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over beets and let set.

title: cheese - stuffed avocado
directions: Slice the avocados in half and remove the pits.
Then take out the pulp and place in a bowl.
Mix the pulp with the baby Gouda cheese, crab meat, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture back into avocado skins.
Garnish with sliced, boiled eggs and fresh parsley.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In a deep microwaveproof bowl, dump (no need to stir, just dump) xxxx sugar, oleo, cocoa, salt and milk.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pan.
Allow to cool.
Cut into squares.
Delicious and easy to make.
Discovered in my microwave recipe book.

title: thick fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with chunk pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix together mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Heat soup.
Add the Knox gelatine, dissolved in 1 teaspoon cold water.
Add soup mixture to cheese mixture.
Add minced or chopped onions to taste and 8 or more ounces crab.
Put in mold; refrigerate.
Spread on crackers.

title: quick cajun onion soup
directions: Fry onions in butter at medium heat for 10 minutes, until tender (not brown).
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water. Add onions; stir well.
Toss croutons in soup bowl and pour hot soup over it.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and add a dash of cayenne pepper.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Beat frosting with beater on high for 10 minutes.
Spread on cake.

title: sweet potato sonker
directions: Place cooked potatoes (well done) in a long pan.
Cook over medium heat.
Add sugar, butter and milk until well mixed and hot. Add flavoring to cooked mixture.

title: beef and beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain; add onion, pepper and celery. Saute about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add beans; simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: fresh apple omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in 3 tablespoons sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Into flour mixture beat milk and egg yolks until smooth.
Gently fold flour mixture into egg whites along with lemon juice, just until combined.
Slowly heat large buttered skillet or griddle (about 10 inches) with metal handle.
Turn batter into skillet, spreading evenly.
Arrange apple slices in pattern over top.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar mixed with cinnamon over top.
Bake about 10 minutes or until top is glazed. Cut into wedges; serve warm.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: rotten coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
After layers cool, split to make 4 layers.

title: ratatouille
directions: Peel and cube zucchini and eggplant.
Place in salt water overnight.
Saute garlic, onions and peppers in a small amount of oil.
Add the rest of the ingredients and allow to simmer for an hour or two.
Serve alone as soup or over pasta as sauce.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pat into a 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat rest of ingredients together and pour over first part.
Bake 25 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Blend all ingredients except nuts together with mixer.
Grease a cookie sheet and line with waxed paper.
Allow waxed paper to extend over both ends of cookie sheet.
Pour batter onto 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly-roll pan; sprinkle nuts on top and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
When baked, turn out onto a linen towel sprinkled with powdered sugar; roll up into towel (jelly-roll style) and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: meat balls and gravy
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, bell pepper, salt, black pepper and dried onion.
Mix into large bowl.
