Roll into a ball-like shape. Place in a deep pan.
Cook until brown.
Place shortening and flour into pan, stirring occasionally, until flour is brown.
Pour 2 cups of water into pan.
When water begins to boil, turn down burner and let simmer for 5 or 10 minutes.

title: garlic broiled fish
directions: Combine the lemon juice, olive oil and seasonings in a bowl. Marinate the fish in this mixture for at least 1 hour or as long as 6 hours (if thin fillets are used, no longer than 1 hour). Place the fish, skin side down, in a baking dish.
Pour the marinade around the fillets and add enough water to cover 3/4 of the fish.
Broil the fish until it flakes easily with a fork.

title: lo-cal punch strawberry slush
directions: In blender, puree strawberries with 1/4 cup pineapple juice. Add Cool Whip.

title: potato soup
directions: In pot, cook onion, celery, carrot and parsley until tender in water to cover.
Add bouillon and 2 cups water.
Add margarine or oil.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in cornstarch, dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
Return to boil, stirring, until clear and slightly thickened.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and add taco seasoning.
Mix meat mixture with the rest of the ingredients and serve.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil spice in tea for awhile, long enough to get all strength out.
Add juices and sugar.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Strain through tea strainer and return to vessel for use.

title: fruit pizza(for use with superstone pie baker)
directions: Roll dough out thin to cover Superstone Baker as pie crust. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, milk and orange juice.
Spread mixture on cooled cookie dough.
Top with fresh fruit arranged in concentric circles.

title: skillet chicken with vegetables
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized chunks.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in olive oil, cook chicken until lightly browned on all sides, stirring often.
Add sweet potatoes, apple juice and seasoning; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add broccoli and continue cooking about 15 minutes longer or until tender.
Mix cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water until smooth; gradually stir into hot liquid in skillet, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly and boils.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip, together and fold in Cool Whip. Put in dish or mold.
Keep in freezer until just before ready to use.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Coat with flour and brown on all sides in hot oil.
Spray a shallow baking dish with Pam and place chicken in, skin side up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drain pineapple juice and add water to make 1 1/4 cups liquid.
In a medium saucepan add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes until thickened.
Pour over chicken and bake 30 minutes. Add pineapple and green pepper slices; bake 30 minutes longer. May be served over rice.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Split your English muffins down the middle; put them on a cookie sheet with insides of muffin facing up.
Put pizza sauce to cover the whole English muffin right to the edges.
Put on each one some mushroom, onion, pepper, sausage, Romano cheese, pepperoni and last Mozzarella.
Sprinkle all on top of each English muffin, then put in oven at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Remove; let cool about 2 minutes. Enjoy.
If you don't like everything on it, put what you like.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add oil.
Then add eggs, one at a time.
Add 7-Up.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: methodist cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line an iron skillet (bottom and sides) with raw bacon.
Combine ingredients and pour into skillet.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° and then 15 minutes at 450°.
Pour off any accumulated fat from bacon.

title: onion soup mix
directions: Mix and store in an airtight container.
Reconstitute by mixing 2 tablespoons mix with 1 cup boiling water.
Simmer 5 to 7 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat and add eggs, sugar and grated, peeled zucchini, oil and vanilla.
Stir until just blended.
Add 1 cup nuts.
Oil and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: 5 baked beans
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, fry bacon and onions until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain grease and stir in brown sugar, vinegar, salts and mustard.
Add beans and simmer about 10 minutes.
Put mixture in a 3-quart casserole dish and bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: betsy ross punch
directions: Put lemonade, pineapple and strawberries in blender.
Blend until completely smooth.
Combine with ginger ale and pour over ice.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine and pound the flour, salt and pepper into the steak. Brown slowly in shortening in a heavy skillet.
Pour tomatoes over meat.
Top with sliced onion.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Cover and bake about 1 hour, until steak is fork-tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spice cupcakes(diabetic recipe)
directions: Line muffin cups with paper baking cups.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, soda and cloves.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well until all dry particles are moistened. Fill prepared muffin cups 1/2 full. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Store in refrigerator.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine in mixer.
Add sugar and vanilla and cream again.
Add flour and beat well.
Roll chips fine.
Add nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peach jello
directions: Heat Jello, pineapple and sugar over low heat until melted. Cool.
Add Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts.
Pour into large dish to refrigerate.

title: sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 9-inch round baking pan melt margarine in oven.
Remove from heat and stir in the next 5 ingredients.
Arrange biscuits in syrup mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until well done.
Let stand in pan for 5 minutes then invert on serving dish.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the potato chips.
Pile lightly into a greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover with the crushed potato chips.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: seven layer bars
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch sheet cake pan, melt butter and sprinkle crumbs over evenly.
Then sprinkle coconut and chips and pour the milk over.
Sprinkle the nuts.
Press lightly and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: different deviled eggs
directions: In a bowl combine all the ingredients except cheese, until creamy. Shape into 1 inch balls. Roll in grated cheese, cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 2 dozen.

title: mom's mincemeat pie
directions: Cook beef roast in salted water for about 3 hours.
Cool. Grind roast in meat grinder or food processor and measure 2 1/2 cups.
Grind peeled and cored apples.
Add to meat and raisins. Add cinnamon and salt; mix together.
If mixture is too thick when mixed, add a little water or apple juice.
Fill prepared pie shell with mixture; add vented top crust.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes longer.

title: mildre's casserole(microwave)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Crumble beef and add onion in glass bowl.
Microwave on High 6 minutes stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Stir in water, corn, tomato paste and seasonings.
Combine 1/2 of meat mixture and noodles in 2 1/2-quart dish.
Mix cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread over meat-noodle mixture.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Microwave on High 12 to 16 minutes.
Rotate dish once halfway through cooking time.

title: mutant scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice very thin.
Dice onion.
Cut butter into approximately 16 pats.
Divide potatoes into fourths, along with onions.
Place 1 layer of potatoes/onion mixture into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 of cheese and place 4 pats of butter on top.
Salt and pepper.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
You will hopefully have 4 layers.
Bake 1 hour in 375° oven. Serve really hot.

title: apple salad
directions: Cut in small pieces and add the other fruit.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: ground beef-cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put beef and remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook for 1 hour stirring now and then. Serve hot with tortilla or corn chips.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.
Pour over all the vegetables.
It will keep in the refrigerator for a few days.

title: angel balls
directions: Mix dates, coconut, white sugar and butter. Cook 6 minutes. Cool. Add Rice Krispies, pecans and vanilla.
Make balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: mexican crescent bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef, onion and seasoning mix. Drain.
Stir in pork and beans.
Separate crescent dough into two rectangles.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides to form crust, sealing perforations.
Spoon meat mixture over crust.
Sprinkle with olives.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Stir in cheese.
Spoon over meat (no need to spread). Bake 25 to 30 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked french toast
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and vanilla in a shallow bowl.
Dip bread into egg mixture turning once and allowing both sides to absorb liquid.
Coat evenly with crumbs and place in a single layer on a well-greased baking sheet.
Drizzle with melted butter. Bake in a 450° oven for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with warm syrup.

title: louisiana beans and rice
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe dish, combine oil, onion, green pepper, garlic, thyme and oregano.
Cover with lid; microwave on high 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once during cooking.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flavorings until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually mix in flour, then fold in sour cream.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan (or you can use several small or two large loaf pans) for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
A big mixer is good to use for this cake.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute pepper, onion and celery until tender. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over crab meat.
Mix with mayo and dressing mix.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: Store in container with tight lid.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut top off peppers; remove seeds and membrane.
Save tops. In a large bowl, combine beef, onion, corn, potatoes and tomatoes. Add salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stuff into peppers; replace tops.

title: parmesan potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking dish, melt butter in oven (5 to 7 minutes).
Stir in salt and pepper. Stir in potatoes until coated with butter.
Cover tightly with foil; bake for 30 minutes.
Remove foil, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Continue baking, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are crisply-tender.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onions and salt; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.
Toss and refrigerate.
This is better if prepared the day before served.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Pat 1/2 of mixture into 9-inch square pan.
Top with rhubarb.
Mix white sugar, water, cornstarch and vanilla.
Bring to boil and cook, stirring until clear.
Pour sauce over rhubarb and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: roast chicken with garlic
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Rinse chicken.
Pat dry.
Place on prepared pan, breast side up.
Put 1 1/2 teaspoons in cavity, sprinkling evenly.
Split 8 cloves and put in cavity.
Peel and mince remaining garlic.
Mix with remaining salt and oregano, oil, cooking wine and pepper in a small dish.
Use your fingers to carefully separate skin from the entire breast area of the chicken without tearing it, making a pocket.
Spoon the garlic mixture into pocket; massage gently on surface to distribute it evenly over breast area.
Roast about 50 minutes.

title: baked sweet onions
directions: Slice onions; cut each slice in half.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter in a Dutch oven until crisp-tender.
Spoon into a lightly greased baking dish.
Spoon into a lightly greased baking dish. Combine soup, half and half, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over onion.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over sauce.
Arrange bread slices on top and brush with 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Simmer sugar, water and coffee until well dissolved.
Remove from heat and let cool until bottom of pan can be touched.
Add vanilla and vodka.
No waiting!
Delicious!

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add rice, soups and water. Stir until all is blended.
Place raw chicken on top of rice mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Remove foil and bake another 15 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve chilled over ice.

title: soda cracker pudding
directions: While warming milk, beat egg yolks and sugar until frothy. Add to hot milk; stir in crackers and coconut.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla. Cool.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beef, salt and pepper.
Pat in bottom of lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with a layer of onion, then a layer of carrots and peas, ending with a layer of potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine soup with water and mix until smooth.
Pour over vegetables and meat.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir over medium heat for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat one egg together with milk.
Add chopped onion and pepper to ground beef.
Mix in tomato paste, then add oats.
Blend until mixture is smooth.
Put into a loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for one hour.
Top with ketchup if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fried veggie batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip veggies into batter and fry until golden brown.
Good for okra, squash, mushrooms and more.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack in jars.
Put 1 pod pepper and 1 clove garlic in each jar.
Combine salt, vinegar and water; heat to boiling.
Pour over okra and seal.
Let stand several weeks before opening.
Makes 10 pints.

title: easy dessert
directions: Place each item as a layer in pan starting with fruit and ending with melted oleo.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana creme supreme
directions: Combine graham crackers, butter and sugar.
Press into bottom and sides of spring-form pan.
Combine whipped topping, pudding and sour cream in bowl.
Pour half of the filling over crust.
Slice bananas and layer on top.
Pour remaining filling over bananas. Finely chop pecans and sprinkle over top.
Refrigerate to chill.

title: pear cake
directions: Chop pears and cover with sugar.
Refrigerate in covered container overnight.
Mix dry ingredients together, then add egg and oil; mix.
Add pears and mix.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cheeseburger bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a 10-inch skillet; drain.
Add the Cheddar cheese soup, milk and frozen vegetables; blend.
Spray or grease generously a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In pan, place 2 cups Bisquick and 3/4 cup water.
Blend spread evenly.
Spread hamburger mixture over batter.
Top with Cheddar cheese, shredded. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Very good!

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter.
Mix butter and dates together.
Add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
(You will have to form it and work with it because at first, it won't stay together.) Then roll ball in powdered sugar.
Makes about 40 balls.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift together flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating at high speed until stiff, glossy peaks form. Blend in vanilla and almond extract.
Add your mixture in 4 parts, folding about 15 strokes after each addition.
Spoon batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Pull metal spatula through batter once to break large air bubbles.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Invert tube pan on funnel or bottle to cool.
When completely cooled, remove from pan.

title: caramel icing
directions: Brown 3 tablespoons sugar in a small heavy skillet, stirring constantly.
While you're browning the sugar, bring all the remaining ingredients, except the vanilla, to a boil.
Add the browned sugar to the other ingredients.
Boil all to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Let cool about 30 minutes.
Beat until creamy.

title: pot roastdallas, texas
directions: Brown roast on both sides in a dutch oven.
Brown onions and add salt, pepper, oregano, thyme, cummin, sage, garlic, etc.
Add water and bake it covered for 2 to 3 hours.
After the meat is done, add sliced carrots and quartered potatoes and more salt and pepper.
Cook another 30 minutes or so until vegetables are done, uncovered if you want browned vegetables.

title: slush
directions: Boil water and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Add the juices to cooled mixture.
Place in freezer.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Add chilies, tomato sauce, soups and taco sauce.
Mix well and heat through.

title: jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients (except meat) into small grinder or food processor.
Grind to release oils.
Put spice into salt shaker.
Cut away all fat and gristle from meat.
Pound with mallet; sprinkle seasoning into meat as you go.

title: chicken salad hawaiian
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Dump berries into large deep dish pie plate.
Sprinkle with 2 tsp. cornstarch.
Mix all other ingredients and spread on fruit. Mix 1 cup sugar with 1 teaspoon cornstarch and top with dough. Pour 1 cup hot water over all.
Bake 375° for 45-55 minutes.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Boil onions or onion rings gently until almost done.
Saute green pepper in 1/4 cup margarine.
Remove peppers from saute pan and add 4 tablespoons flour and 2 cups milk to make a medium white sauce.
Place onions and peppers together with white sauce in a baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: shrimp-crab spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion, celery, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, lemon juice, 1/4 cup cocktail sauce and shrimp.
Form into a roll and chill.
Spread with more cocktail sauce and shred crab on top. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken country captain
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown well in oil and keep warm (secret of recipe).
Saute onions, peppers and garlic.
Stir in curry, salt, pepper and thyme and mix well.
Add tomatoes and parsley and heat.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into 1/4 x 1-inch pieces. Brown meat in oil.
Push meat to one side.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Stir on stove in saucepan:
flour, margarine, milk and Velveeta cheese until melted and creamy.
Cook elbows and drain. Pour cheese mixture and elbows into 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 20 minutes, uncovered, at 400°.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add water and vegetables of choice.
Fresh or frozen or both.
Cook until all vegetables are done.

title: watercress salad
directions: Cut watercress in 1-inch lengths after washing.
Blanch watercress in a pot of boiling water; then drain well.
In a bowl mix watercress, tomato slices and patis.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter and sugars together. Add vanilla, peanut butter and eggs. Mix well. Add cocoa; mix well. Add flour and soda; mix well. Fold in chips and Reese's. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool 1 to 2 minutes on sheet before removing to wire rack to cool completely.

title: funnel cake or drechter kucha
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs with milk and add to flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Heat shortening to 375°.
Hold funnel over hot shortening, holding spout closed with finger. Pour batter into funnel.
Allow batter to flow through funnel into hot shortening, moving funnel to form a coil pattern.
Fry about 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm.
This recipe makes 6 to 9 funnel cakes.

title: easy-delicious swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie pan (or use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and double recipe) 2/3 full of peeled and sliced apples.
Then sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cream and syrup until soft ball stage.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Beat with electric beater for 10 to 12 minutes. Mixture will become creamy.
Add nuts and stir well.

title: bill's northern chunky chicken and dumplings
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Pour chicken broth and water in large pot with lid.
Boil chicken until done (25 minutes approximately).
Remove chicken from water.
Add to boiling water, celery, pepper, salt, onion, carrots and peppers.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Pull chicken meat from bones in pieces and put back in pot.
Add 1/2 can water, white potatoes and mushrooms.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add dumplings.

title: crispy baked catfish(serves 4)
directions: May substitute seasoned salt for the paprika, salt and red and black pepper.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix dill seed, celery seed, onion salt, garlic salt, onion flakes, parsley flakes, sour cream and mayonnaise together. Chill overnight.
Cut center out of rye bread and fill with dill dip.

title: grandma geary's yeast rolls
directions: Combine hot water and yeast in large bowl and let sit 5 minutes.
Combine all the other ingredients with 3 cups flour.
Mix with yeast mixture.
Knead on floured board, then form into a log roll.
Cut into golf ball size pieces and place in greased muffin pans.
Cover with warm wet cloth and allow to rise until double in size about 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: breakfast coffee ring
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in milk and butter or oleo.
Sift sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add dry ingredients and orange rind to milk mixture, stirring only until well blended.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch ring mold.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on rack for 5 minutes; remove from pan.
When cool, drizzle confectioners sugar icing over top. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Makes one 9-inch ring.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: In heavy 10-inch skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add apples and cook over medium heat until apples are just tender. Stir occasionally.

title: graham squares
directions: Crush graham crackers to a mealy flour.
Add baking powder. Stir in milk, salt, chips and vanilla.
Spread in pan like brownies.
Bake 25 minutes in 325° oven.
Cut in squares when cool.
Nuts may be added, if desired.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Combine ingredients and serve with bread.
This butter keeps several days in refrigerator.
Serve butter at room temperature.

title: breakfast cinnamon cake
directions: Cream shortening, then add all of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: cold veggie pizza
directions: Spread strips of rolls onto cookie sheet or flat dish.
Bake according to directions and let cool.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together - including juices.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350 for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey chili with zucchini
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic for 2 minutes.
Add turkey, browning well.
Add tomatoes.
Stir in beans, corn, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add chopped zucchini.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: apple brownies
directions: Beat melted margarine, sugar and egg in large bowl. Add grated apples and chopped nuts.
Sift together dry ingredients and fold into apple mixture. Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan 50 minutes at 350°.

title: onion salad
directions: Peel and slice onions and set aside.
Make marinade of the water, sugar, vinegar and salt; boil.
Pour boiling hot over the prepared onions and keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: mock pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, oregano and 1/2 of sauce. Pat into pie plate on bottom and up on sides.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, drain fat and spoon remaining sauce over top of meat.
Cut cheese into triangles and place on sauce. Sprinkle oregano over cheese and put back in oven for 7 minutes.

title: brandied peaches flambe
directions: Put small servings of ice cream in individual serving dishes and place in freezer.
Drain peach halves; warm syrup in a saucepan and flavor to taste with a small amount of brandy.
Warm remaining brandy in a separate saucepan.
Arrange the peach halves in a broiler-proof dish, cut side up and place a dab of butter and 1 tablespoon brown sugar in the center of each peach.
Broil 3 inches from heat until sugar melts and peaches are heated.
Place a peach half on each dish of ice cream and top with heated syrup.
Pour heated brandy over peaches and ignite.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: mouth watering roast
directions: Place all ingredients in Dutch oven tightly.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a large bowl; set aside.
Bring to a boil, cocoa, oleo and Coca-Cola; pour over flour mixture. Separately, beat together eggs, soda and buttermilk; add marshmallows and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat well. Place in greased and floured tube or 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: blueberry upside-down cake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine berries, 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and juice.
Spread mixture on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 2 cups flour and baking powder; set aside. Cream shortening in a large bowl.
Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk.
Fold in nuts and orange rind.

title: lemon bars
directions: Pour onto crust.
Bake 25 minutes before center is set.
While cooling, sift powdered sugar over top.
Cut into bars.

title: monkey faced cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; mix in molasses.
Stir vinegar into sour milk and mix into sugar mix.
Mix flour and seasonings together; mix into sugar and milk mixture.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet, 2 1/2 inches apart.
Place 3 raisins for 2 eyes and 1 mouth.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let cheese soften at room temperature; combine cheeses and onion and blend.
Stir in parsley and nuts; place in bowl and chill.
Shape into balls and roll in parsley and nuts.
Wrap and freeze if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick and easy skillet dinner
directions: Cook sausage in 12-inch skillet over medium heat 2 minutes. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add rice; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients except green pepper.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and dice apples; set aside.
Pour oil in bowl and add sugar and eggs. Beat well.
Mix dry ingredients and gradually add to the creamed mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in oblong cake pan or tube pan for about 1 hour.
Test with a straw.
This is a good, moist cake and does not require icing unless desired.

title: tuna salad with pasta and grapes
directions: Toss ingredients together and chill several hours before serving.
Recipe may be made with diced chicken replacing the tuna.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and the sugars until completely blended. Add the beaten eggs and the vanilla.
Beat this into the creamed shortening and sugar.
Sift the salt, baking soda and flour; add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add the oatmeal and nuts; stir until well blended.
Take a handful of the dough and form into a long roll (make several).
Wrap the rolls in waxed paper.
Label and refrigerate.
Chill thoroughly before baking.

title: cheese strata
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put half of cubes and cheese in pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup of meat and mushrooms over bread and cheese.
Repeat.
Pour milk, eggs and seasoning over all.
Let stand overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Check after 45 minutes. Should not be wobbly.
Serve with fruit and sweet rolls.

title: tomato aspic salad(serves four)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O into heated tomato juice and add all other ingredients and pour into a 4-cup mold.
Place into refrigerator until set.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well, beating eggs after each addition.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie 2
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones and place into the bottom of a 9 X 13 baking dish.
Mix soup and broth in bowl and pour over chicken.
Add vegetables.
In a separate bowl, cut margarine into flour with
fork until crumbly.
Add milk. Drizzle evenly over chicken and broth mixture. Bake at 350 until golden brown.
Serve hot from the oven.

title: crunchy coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, combine cabbage, walnuts, raisins and carrots. For the dressing, in medium size bowl, whisk together sour cream, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice, honey, salt and pepper; pour over cabbage mixture.
Stir until well mixed; cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: sweet sour baked beans
directions: Brown bacon; drain and crumble.
Empty frying pan and put onions, brown sugar, dry mustard, salt, garlic powder and cider vinegar in skillet and simmer covered 20 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: margie tose's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, peanut butter and sugars until very creamy.
Add eggs and beat until combined and smooth.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Mix on low speed just until combined.
Chill dough until firm about 2 hours.
Roll by rounded teaspoons into a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork in a crisscross pattern dipped in flour so it doesn't stick.
Bake at 375° until set but not hard, 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli and add to the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: arkansas cumin rice
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and rice in the vegetable oil until golden brown in a 2-quart ovenproof baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger; drain excess grease.
Add chilies, onion, water and taco seasoning and simmer about 15 minutes.
Mix cornbread, corn, eggs and milk.
Pour 1/2 mixture into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Top with hamburger mix and cheese.
Add rest of cornbread mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese vegetable casserole
directions: Cook first 4 vegetables in just enough water to cover until tender.
Add peas.
Make white sauce with butter, flour and milk. Add Cheddar cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add cottage cheese. Combine with vegetables.
Pour into 2-quart buttered baking dish. Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Put in the bottom of a pie plate; top with taco sauce, then tomatoes.
Add optional ingredients if you'd like.

title: low-fat stuffed manicotti
directions: Mix spinach with onions, nutmeg and parsley.
Mash cottage cheese and blend with milk.
Add to spinach mixture.
Mix in beaten egg white.
Stuff shells with mixture.

title: bert's sausage balls
directions: Combine stuffing mix, 1/2 cup water, sausage, butter and egg in a bowl, mixing well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Wrap bacon around each; secure with a pick.
Place on a rack in a baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs (one at a time).
Add flour, 7-Up and extract.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (or longer).

title: low-fat salad
directions: Prepare salad dressing mix, vinegar, orange juice and water as directed on envelope.
Substitute the orange juice for the water and add the orange peel.
Mix spinach, oranges, onion and meat or crab in bowl.
Add dressing and toss lightly.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of salad for added flavor.
Serve immediately.

title: homemade fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add other and bake in greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples in small amount of water until done.
Put in blender until smooth.
For each cup of apple pulp, add the sugar, cinnamon and cloves in heavy pan.
Cook until thick and glossy. Put in jars and seal.

title: holiday tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour mixture into boiling water to taste.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix together tomato soup, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Pour over mixed vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: stovetop mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat in 10 inch skillet.
Add beans, salsa and rice in layers.
Then add water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Turn off heat.
Sprinkle cheese over top and cover.
Let set 15 minutes. Serve with corn chips.
Serves 6.

title: corn relish
directions: In a small saucepan, heat sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed, vinegar and Tabasco to boiling; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Cool and refrigerate in covered bowl.
Let stand overnight.
Makes 2 cups.

title: whole wheat banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine bananas and buttermilk or yogurt, stirring just enough to mix.
Add dry ingredients alternately with banana mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cooling rack.

title: grandmommie's fig berry jam
directions: Mash figs; add sugar and jello.
Bring to a boil and boil for 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash and onion; cook in water until tender.
Remove from heat, mash and drain.
Then add all other ingredients and stir vigorously.
Pour into a greased casserole baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: raisin brown bread
directions: Let set on counter (cover with plastic bag) overnight.
Bake in the morning at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cornish hens
directions: Cook rice by directions, adding bouillon cube with rice and seasoning envelope. Remove giblets from hens and reserve for another use. Rinse hens with cold water and pat dry. Saute onion and celery in oleo; add mushrooms and cook 1 to 2 minutes. Combine rice, vegetables, lemon rind and poultry seasoning, stirring well. Stuff hens lightly with rice mixture. Close cavity. Combine next 6 ingredients, stirring well. Brush hens with soy sauce mixture and place breast side up in pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Baste often with soy sauce mixture.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix together cherries. Spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix Bisquick, nuts, sugar and cinnamon together.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cherry mix.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In mixing bowl combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper. Gently stir in beans.
Spoon half of the mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of the onions.
Spoon remaining bean mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with remaining onions.
Return to oven for 5 minutes or until onions are brown and crispy. Yields 10 servings.

title: randy's velveeta enchiladas
directions: Brown meat in skillet; add salt and pepper.
Grate cheese and chop onions; set aside.
Make white sauce using flour, margarine, salt and milk.
When thickened, add Velveeta.
Remove from heat.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Grease and flour 18 x 12 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Melt together 1 cup margarine, water and the first measurement of cocoa; bring to boil (can be done in microwave).
Using wire whisk, blend the granulated sugar, salt, flour, baking soda, eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla and soured milk.
Blend into first mixture. Pour onto pan; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While cake bakes, prepare icing.

title: classic tuna casserole(serves 6)
directions: Empty tuna into
casserole.
Add
milk	and mix.
Add 1 cup potato chips, tuna and peas to soup.
Stir well.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top.
Bake in 350° oven 20 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, chili beans and Sloppy Joe mix.
Mix well and let simmer until hot.
Serves 5.

title: pumpkin-spice bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2x10 1/2x1 inches.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Stir in flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, ginger and cloves.
Mix in raisins.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake until light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into bars, about 2x1 1/2 inches.
Refrigerate any remaining bars.
Makes about four dozen bars.

title: u love it pudding
directions: Mix together in a bowl the first 9 ingredients. Place in a 9-inch square pan and do not grease the pan.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mix.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: summer chili
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces; brown in olive oil.
Slice zucchini and chop onion and garlic and add to chicken.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes and add kidney beans, tomatoes and seasonings and cook 30 minutes.
You may add any summer vegetables you like.
I like to triple the recipe and freeze part of it.

title: cauliflower
directions: Separate head in florets.
Heat margarine.
Add cauliflower and seasonings.
Saute until golden (7 to 8 minutes).
Add crumbs; continue cooking for 3 to 4 minutes.
Toss frequently until crisp and golden.

title: christmas white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar to soft fluffy stage; add beaten egg yolks and whip.
Sift flour and baking powder together three times and add to mixture.
Alternate with milk.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites, vanilla and lemon extract.
Wash raisins; dry thoroughly. Dredge in flour, also fruits.
Work in fruits.
Coarsely chop almonds.
Stir well; work in coconut.
Bake in slow oven for 2 1/2 hours in paper-lined greased tins.

title: monroe's pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle 1 teaspoon flour and 1 teaspoon sugar in the bottom of each pie shell.
Beat eggs lightly in bowl with a fork.
Cook sugar, margarine and corn syrup to a rolling bowl.
Pour into eggs. Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
More pecans can be added if desired.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: smoky brisket
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Marinate covered brisket in liquid for 24 hours.
Place brisket in pan with juice and cook, covered, 5 hours at 300°.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add cream and flour alternately.
After pouring cake batter into pan, sprinkle generously with coconut.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300° in tube pan.
The toasted coconut icing has a flavor if its own and no additional icing is needed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: incrediveggies
directions: Wash all veggies. Blanch broccoli flowerets, carrots and bok choy.
In a 3-quart microwave-safe dish, combine all veggies and drizzle with marmalade, basil and lemon juice.
Cover tightly and microwave on High for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add eggs and enough water to make stiff dough.
Roll out on floured surface until very thin.
Cut into 1-inch strips.
Have chicken broth boiling and salted to taste. Pinch dumpling strips into small bits and drop into boiling broth. Cook about 10 minutes, then add chicken.

title: chicken with paprika gravy
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add browned cubed bacon.
Cut chicken breasts in pieces.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add to onions and bacon with a little water.
Cook until done.
Add sour cream; thicken with flour.
Add paprika (mix paprika with a little water until dissolved).
Simmer until creamy and chicken is done.
Pour this over dumplings of your choice or noodles.
(One of Woody's favorite Bohemian dinners.)

title: beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cooks in about 4 hours. May need to stir during cooking.

title: hamburger-hot dish divine
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onions.
Layer beef in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with hash browns.
Mix soup with sour cream; pour over potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a large pot, cook cut up chicken.
Dice celery and onion; add to pot.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.
Let cook until chicken is done (falls apart).
Remove chicken and clean from bones.
Cut up in bite-size pieces and return to the pot.
Peel about 6 to 10 potatoes; quarter and put into the pot.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown 4 pork chops. Peel and slice 4 medium potatoes thin. Mix 2 Tbsp. flour, 2 tsp. salt, and 1/2 tsp. pepper.
Pour over the potatoes.
Dot with a Tbsp. of butter.
Pour the 1 cup milk (cream or canned milk) over the potatoes.
Lay the pork chops on top. Bake covered at 400 degrees for 45 minutes.
Remove the lid and bake an additional 15 minutes or until the potatoes are brown.

title: hazel feroe's date nut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir in.
Mix in walnuts and dates.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan. Bake until top crust is dull.
Cut while warm.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute butter, celery, onion and bell pepper.
Cook macaroni. Add tomatoes to vegetables.
Saute for 15 minutes. Add soup, chicken and macaroni to vegetables.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Put in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
You can put sliced olives and grated cheese on top.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla and nutmeg, in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened (about 20 minutes), stirring several times.
Take pudding off burner and add vanilla.
Spoon into small bowls and sprinkle nutmeg on top. Serve warm or cold.
Makes 3 servings.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain marinade from one jar of artichokes into a 9 x 9-inch microwave-proof dish or 10-inch quiche dish.
Drain remaining marinade.
Chop artichokes; set aside.
Add onion and garlic to marinade in dish and microcook, covered, 1 to 2 minutes, until onion is soft.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, using package directions; drain.
Add soup, cheese, mayo, onion and eggs; mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nana's german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; set aside and cool.
Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add egg yolks one at a time; beat well after each.
Sift soda, salt and flour (do not use salt if using self-rising flour) together.
Beat in chocolate, then add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk; beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: crab stuffed chicken
directions: Place each chicken piece between 2 pieces of waxed paper and pound lightly to 1/8-inch thick.
In saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons of the butter; blend in the flour.
Add milk, broth and wine all at once.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Set aside.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand.
Pour into sprayed sheet cake pan (11 x 17-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry nutbread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a "well" in the center.
Put in remaining ingredients and stir until moistened.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 60 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: chocolate tea bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream till light and fluffy; add eggs and beat well. Add milk to vinegar. Mix and sift together flour, salt, soda and cocoa. Stir in nuts. Add to creamed mixture alternately with liquids, beating until blended after each addition. Pour into greased small loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven (350 degrees) for 1 hour. Cool. Wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft, not brown.
Add garlic.
Rinse beans well with water.
Chop beans and artichoke hearts fine.
Add to onion and garlic.
Mix well and saute for a while.
Add bread crumbs and cheese.
Note:
This is better if fixed the day before. Bake in 350° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine butter, sugar and egg, mix well. Add flour and stir until blended. Add vanilla and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet. Press to 1/8-inch thickness. Bake at 325 degrees for 8-10 minutes or until brown.

title: uncle jason's corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish with cooking spray, butter or margarine.
In a large bowl, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add eggs, corn and milk to sugar mixture; stir until blended.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake.
Cool and split layers before frosting.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together in large bowl and beat 2 minutes.
Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 300° oven.

title: biddy beans
directions: Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper.
Combine all ingredients in a 6-quart crock-pot or slow cooker and cook for several hours.

title: pasta salad medley
directions: Pour dressing over combined noodles and vegetables.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator several hours.
Drain.
Combine salad dressing and cheese; mix well.
Add to vegetable mixture; mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
20 minutes; chilling time:
3 to 4 hours.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in butter.
Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and beat 5 minutes more.
Then add vanilla, milk and syrup; mix well, then add pecans.
Mix and pour into ice cream freezer.
Add milk to fill line, then freeze.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into balls.
Fry in oil until brown. Put meatballs in sauce and cook for 2 hours on low.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Peel the potatoes and cut into 1/4 x 1/4 x 3-inch strips.
Pour the oil into a wide 1 or 2-quart bowl. Toss the potato strips in the oil.
Shake off any excess oil, then place the strips on an ungreased baking pan.
Sprinkle them with onion powder or one of the other seasonings.
Bake for 20 minutes or until one side of the potato strips are brown.
Turn them over and bake until brown and crisp on the other side, about 10 more minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper towels.
Yield:
makes 50 to 60 fries and serves 6.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, cream and vanilla. Separately mix flour, brown sugar, pecans and butter together and top sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: homemade sweet pickles
directions: Wash and peel cucumbers. Slice and put in pan. Add a pinch of salt and mix together. Cover with ice cubes on top of slices for about 2 hours. Drain water and add vinegar and sugar and the rest of the seasoning. Boil for 15 minutes and let cool.

title: bloody mary dip
directions: Beat cheese and ketchup until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables and water until half tender (in microwave, 12 to 17 minutes).
Add broth and milk and cook until just done (in microwave, 6 to 8 minutes).
Stir in cheese and cook until melted.

title: italian crescent bake
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and mushrooms; drain off grease. Add tomato sauce.
Pour into an 8 x 11-inch dish.
Top with cheese.
Separate rolls.
Mix sour cream, oregano and basil. Spread 1 tablespoon mixture on each roll and roll up.
Place on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 375° until rolls are brown (about 20 minutes).
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix dressing with enough broth to mixture.
Place in casserole on melted butter.
Spread chicken over dressing.
Mix soups; warm and pour over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Melt margarine in a casserole baking dish.
In a bowl mix flour, milk and sugar.
Pour into baking dish over melted margarine.
Gently spoon drained peaches over top of flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: old-fashioned vegetable beef soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large stew pot.
Simmer for 3 hours, covered.
Enjoy.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Split English muffins and toast in toaster.
Spoon 1 tablespoon pizza sauce on each muffin half.
Top with pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 425° for 7 minutes.
Makes 12 pizzas.

title: peas oriental
directions: Whip soup with wire whisk.
Add all ingredients, except onions.
Put in long buttered casserole; top with onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Chicken or cooked shrimp can be added to make a main dish.

title: overnight caramel coffee ring
directions: Lightly grease a large Bundt or fluted cake pan.
Layer frozen rolls in pan.
Mix cinnamon with sugar and pour over rolls. Layer, one at a time, chopped nuts, brown sugar and dry pudding mix.
Slice margarine and place around rolls.
Cover pan with cloth and set in warm, draft-free place overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Invert pan; let set a few minutes, then remove so sugar syrup covers cake.
Best when served hot, but tastes fresh baked when reheated in the microwave.
Serves 10 to 14.

title: carrot ring or copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Make layer of carrots, onions, and pepper in a large bowl.
Mix all other ingredients well with mixer.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate 2 days for flavor. Serve chilled.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: leftover mashed potatoes
directions: To the leftover mashed potatoes, add some milk and a dash of horseradish.
Add some table mustard and a few fried bacon chips. Whip it up.
Spread a layer in the bottom of a greased casserole and grate some cheese over it.
Add the rest of the mashed potatoes over that and top with more grated cheese.
Bake it in the oven with a piece of foil over it until the potatoes are hot. Remove foil and let the cheese brown a bit.

title: chocolate chip-butterscotch cookies
directions: Beat eggs, water, margarine and vanilla and 1/2 of dry cake mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining dry cake mix and chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Spread in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.
(Can also be dropped by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets and baked about 6 minutes.)

title: spanish rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except rice in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add rice.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Pepper to taste.

title: super bowl dip
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Melt cheese.
Combine meat, melted cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Serve with chips.
Keep warm.

title: grandma's maple frosting
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer above ingredients in oven-proof bowl.

title: freezer strawberry preserves
directions: Measure fruit and lemon juice into crock-pot.
Stir well. Sprinkle in package of Sure-Jell, stirring vigorously.
Set aside 30 minutes, stirring mixture once in a while.
Then add 1 cup syrup and mix well.
Then stir sugar into fruit mixture.
Warm to 100°, no hotter.
When sugar is dissolved preserves are ready to pour into glasses or jars.
Chill 24 hours in refrigerator, then place in freezer to store.
Makes 4 pints.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat
salad
oil and eggs until frothy.
Blend in sugar and vanilla.
Gradually
add
flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Blend well.
Fold
in
apples
and
nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water as directed.
Add frozen orange juice and mandarin oranges.
Congeal.

title: sugarless banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at about 325° for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese and tuna salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
This is a good diet meal.
It's full of good vegetables and no mayonnaise.
You can change or add any vegetable.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, sugar, cocoa and milk; heat to boiling and boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir briskly, then drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain grease.
Spray 9 x 13-inch casserole with vegetable spray.
Place layer of tortillas on bottom of pan.
Put a layer of ground beef over tortillas.
Put on layer of beans, then a layer of cheese.
Place another layer of tortillas on.
Repeat layers of meat, beans and cheese.
Next, spread Ro-Tel tomatoes or picante sauce over layers.
Spread cream of chicken soup next.
Top with another layer of cheese and a final layer of tortillas.

title: ambrosia
directions: Save juice from both fruits to serve as a beverage.
In a medium size bowl, combine all ingredients except yogurt.
Fold in yogurt and chill.

title: spinach souffle
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cottage cheese and eggs.
Add spinach, 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese and salt.
Spoon into greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese and let stand 5 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: snickers cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour half of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Melt caramels, butter and milk in double boiler.
Remove cake from oven.
Pour caramel mixture over it.
Top with chocolate chips and pecans.
Dot remaining cake batter over top and return to oven at 250° for 20 minutes.
Then turn oven to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: frozen pudding sandwiches
directions: Gradually add milk to peanut butter; blend until smooth.
Add pudding and blend with mixer, about 2 minutes.
Spread 1/2-inch thick on 12 crackers and top with 12 crackers.
Smooth edge with spatula and freeze until firm.

title: cracklin corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in greased frying pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat sugar and syrup enough to dissolve the sugar.
Add the other ingredients; mix and press down in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
No cooking!

title: pea salad(instead of peas, try a pea salad.)
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pasta primavera with three cheeses
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
In a 12-inch skillet, cook peppers, squash and mushrooms in margarine for 3 to 4 minutes until almost tender.
Drain pasta.
Toss with vegetables in skillet.
Transfer to heated platter, cover to keep warm.
In medium saucepan, combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, milk, Parmesan, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until warm (do not boil).
Spoon over pasta and vegetables.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken,
almonds,
onion, celery, mayonnaise, salt and lemon juice.
Place
in
buttered baking dish.
Top with a layer of cheese,
then
cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot; is tender.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: beans 'n beef
directions: Brown beef; sprinkle with salt and pepper in the shortening. When beef is done, drain off excess fat.
Add mustard, ketchup and beans.
Stir well.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
Could serve on hamburger buns.
Freezes well.

title: strawberry julius
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: new york pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, milk and eggs and beat lightly; batter should be lumpy.
Place 12-inch skillet (ovenproof handle) over medium heat and melt butter.
Tilt pan to coat bottom and sides.
Increase heat to high.
When butter bubbles, pour batter into pan.
Remove from heat and place in oven for 18 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Each pancake serves 2 people.

title: deluxe sugar cookies
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add egg and flavorings; cream well.
Add all dry ingredients together.
Blend thoroughly with creamed mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: glazed peach pie
directions: Crush enough peaches to make 1 cup, leaving rest sliced. Combine crushed peaches with water, sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil and cook over low heat until clear (2 or 3 minutes), stirring occasionally, then add butter.
Cool slightly.
Line baked pie shell with fresh peach slices.
Pour glaze mixture over peach slices.
Chill for 2 hours or more.

title: ham steaks in port sauce
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat. Slice extra fat off ham.
Add ham steak and quickly brown on both sides.
Add Port and let bubble for a moment.
Add stock, mushrooms and green onions.
Simmer gently, basting ham with sauce until mushrooms are tender (about 5 minutes).
Remove ham and reduce sauce by half.
Add ham; heat 1 minute and serve.
Great with poached or scrambled eggs!
Serves 2 to 4.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a square pan.
In a large bowl, cream butter and add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, dry frosting mix and nuts until well blended.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to an hour.
Let cool 1 hour before cutting.

title: margie's cheese cake
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix with butter.
Line bottom of pan for crust.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup of hot water; let cool.

title: margaret's "apricot bread"
directions: Soak apricots in warm water 30 minutes.
Drain and cut in quarters.
Cream butter, sugar and egg; blend in apricots and orange juice.
Add dry ingredients.

title: frozen sandwich
directions: Add milk to peanut butter and blend until smooth.
Add pudding. On low speed, beat 1 to 2 minutes until smooth.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread 1/2-inch thick on 12 crackers.
Top with remaining crackers.
Press lightly and smooth around edges with spatula. Freeze until firm (about 3 hours).
Can be stored wrapped in freezer for 3 to 4 days.
Healthy, tasty dessert or snack for little ones.

title: pecan-pie surprise bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set aside 3/4 cup cake mix.
In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining cake mix, butter or margarine and 1 egg; mix with fork until crumbly.
Press crumbs into the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: meat pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onions until meat is brown.
Spoon off drippings.
Stir in soup, milk, soy sauce and salt; heat through.
Gently stir in olives and parsley.
Pour mixture into baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Prepare 1/2 recipe Bisquick biscuit dough from basic recipe.
Roll dough into square, 7 x 7-inches.
Cut square into 1-inch strips.
Place strips over meat mixture.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together, except olives.
Chill dough 15 or 20 minutes. Mound dough around olives or make ball out of dough.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Overloading your fireplace can cause a black, sooty stain on your fireplace face.
For brick, stone or other masonry products, there are two solutions to remove stains.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Add the milk.
Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and rhubarb and stir into egg mixture.
Put in pie shell, dot with oleo.
Bake at 350°.

title: k f c buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine ingredients; knead until smooth. Roll out dough to 3/4-inch thick. Cut out biscuits. Bake on greased baking sheet 12 minutes or until brown. Makes 18 biscuits.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Stew meat in 2 cups of water for about 2 hours or until meat pulls apart easily.
Drain well. Cover with sauce and serve on buns.

title: dill dip for vegetables
directions: Mix and if it is too thick, add some juice from the olives.

title: quick blueberry pie-cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into pan and add blueberries on top of mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Brown lightly.

title: baked ham
directions: Wash and soak.
Prepare for cooking.
Remove skin.
Add 5 cups water to roaster with lid.
Put in oven.
Set temperature to 500° and bake 15 minutes.
Turn oven off 3 hours.
Do not open oven door.
Put back in oven set at 500° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Leave in oven overnight.
Do not open door.
By morning, your ham is cooked.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Slice washed potatoes; place in greased casserole.
Cut oleo in pieces; distribute evenly over potatoes.
Mix contents of onion soup mix; sprinkle half over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bobbie jean's cranberry bread
directions: In mixing bowl, beat egg.
Add sugar and oil.
In 1-cup measure, squeeze orange to extract juice.
Grate rind.
Fill cup with boiling water to make 1 cup liquid.
Add to sugar mixture. Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Blend quickly. Add whole cranberries and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured pan. Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Turn off oven and let set 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake until rhubarb is tender at 350°.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute veggies in a small amount of olive oil until tender-crisp.
Add drained tomatoes.
Drain all in a colander. Micro-melt cheese.
Add veggies and mix.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: party candy strawberries
directions: Mix nuts, coconut and gelatin in a bowl.
Stir in milk, vanilla and enough food coloring for strawberry color.
Chill overnight.
Shape into strawberries using about 1 teaspoon mixture for each strawberry.
Roll each berry in additional gelatin.
Let stand until dry.
Using green frosting, shape leaves on each strawberry.
Makes 80 to 100 small strawberries.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in hot oven at 375° until done.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain well. Combine the remaining ingredients in a crock-pot and add beef.
Stir well. Cook on low for 4 hours.
(If in a pot on the stove, simmer for 1 hour.)

title: parmesan cheese puffs
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on bread rounds (whole wheat).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: pickled eggs on greens
directions: Place peeled eggs in glass bowl on jar.
Mix remaining ingredients except greens.
Pour over eggs.
Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors, at least 2 days.
Cut eggs crosswise into slices; serve on greens.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until tender; remove meat from bones and let cool, then chop real fine.
Mix celery, pickles and eggs.
Add mayonnaise and mix all together.

title: maple nut pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup hot water.
Add to scalded milk, then add syrup and mix well.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
When cooled so that it is thick enough to roll from a spoon, add whip cream and pecans.
In the meantime crush vanilla wafers.
Place half the crumbs in an oblong dish.
Put the pudding over this.
Add the rest of crumbs over the pudding.
Refrigerate until firm set, better if left overnight.

title: pepper steak(this is a delicious meat dish.)
directions: Mix garlic, soy sauce and ginger in a bowl.
Cut round steak into strips and soak in mixture for 10 minutes.
In a large skillet, heat oil and over high heat, toss beef until brown.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes, celery and green pepper; cook, tossing once in awhile, for 15 minutes or until tender.
In a small bowl, mix cornstarch with water, add to steak dish and stir. Serve on fluffy rice.
Serves 6.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: turtle fudge cheese cake
directions: Crumble Oreos and mix with 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Put into 9-inch spring-form pan and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: irish champ with crispy onions
directions: Melt butter in frying pan and cook onions until nicely browned.

title: breakfast tequito
directions: Brown sausage in large pot.
Brown potatoes in separate pan with butter or oil.
Scramble eggs.
Mix all cooked ingredients in large pan.
Place mixture with desired amount of cheese in flour tortillas.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon (save liquor for sauce).
Remove bones and break into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form loaf and bake in 8 1/2-inch loaf pan at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly brown.
Turn on platter and serve with Salmon Sauce.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, add sherbet and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until set.

title: haluska(ha-lou-sh-ka)
directions: Chop cabbage and onion.
Melt butter or margarine in large frypan and add cabbage and onions.
Cook until tender, turning often.
Cook small flat noodles about 7 minutes in water and drain.
Add to cabbage and onions.
Season to taste.
Cover and set aside until rest of meal is ready.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and let sit overnight.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Mix remaining 6 ingredients. Bring to boil.
Spray casserole pan with Pam.
Tear tortillas in bite-size pieces.
Add layer of hamburger.
Pour soup mixture on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: fajitas pronto
directions: Combine picante sauce, green onions, cilantro, oil, lemon juice, garlic and salt in bowl; mix well.
Combine 1/4 cup sauce with beans in bowl.
Combine 1/4 cup sauce with tomatoes and avocado in bowl.
Chill bean mixture and tomato mixture in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: apple pie and crust
directions: Mix until all worked together with a pastry blender.
Slowly add cold water and mix into a ball that is soft and rollable with a fork.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Combine flour and seasonings in a large bag.
Place meat in the bag and shake to coat.
Brown meat in a skillet.
Add onion, garlic salt and mushrooms.
Saute until partially tender.
Add liquids and Worcestershire sauce; bring to a boil.
Either continue to simmer for about 90 minutes or place in a crock-pot and cook 4 to 6 hours.
Add sour cream after meat is tender (last 20 minutes of cooking).
Serve over hot noodles.

title: cranberry carrots
directions: Place carrots in water in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart microwave-proof casserole.
Cover and place in microwave on High (600 to 700 watts) for about 9 minutes; drain.
Stir in margarine and cranberry sauce; season with salt.
Cover and place back in the oven at Medium-high (400 to 500 watts) for about 2 minutes.
Stir. Cover.
Cook on Medium-high about 1 minute.
Yields 4 servings.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Mix milk, chips and margarine together.
Melt in microwave (approximately 1 to 2 minutes).
After melted, stir well and add peanuts and marshmallows.
Pour into greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Let cool in fridge.
Cut into squares.
Eat and enjoy.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
Grind the cranberries in blender.
Grind the tangelos.
Mix the sugar, celery and nuts with the other ingredients.

title: maple baked beans
directions: Place beans, syrup, onion and mustard in a dish.
Cover with cut-up bacon pieces (2 or 3 strips).
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Turn on broiler the last 5 minutes if bacon isn't brown enough.

title: witch's brew
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; bring to a slow boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes; strain.
Chill; pour in ginger ale just before serving.

title: ted's swiss cheese soup
directions: Melt butter and add flour.
Add milk and chicken stock to make a roux, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil; let simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in Cheez Whiz and Swiss, stirring constantly. Simmer 15 minutes; add salt and pepper to taste.
Just before serving, add wine and simmer one minute more.
After dishing out, add a dash of Kirschwasser on top of each serving (optional).

title: party mix
directions: Mix both cereals, pretzels and nuts.
Melt butter.
Stir in garlic powder, lemon juice and
worcestershire sauce.
Pour butter mixture over cereal mixture to thoroughly coat it.
Bake 250 degrees for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: perfect spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease a 9x13 glass pan and set aside.
Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices together.
Blend thoroughly and set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add the sugars, creaming until fluffy.
Add the beaten eggs in halves, beating thoroughly after each one.
Add 1/3 dry ingredients and 1/3 of the buttermilk, mix thoroughly and repeat until each is gone.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake for 55 - 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Try topping with a cream cheese icing or enjoy this treat just as it is.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let set 3 hours or overnight; drain.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil.
Add vegetables.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Bottle and seal.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Melt margarine; add sugar.
Mix well.
Sift in flour alternating with eggs.
Add chips and nuts; toss lightly.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: kylee's fabulous lemonade
directions: To make 4 1/2 quarts, squeeze the lemons.
Add sugar to the lemon juice. (Always add the sugar before the water.
That's the secret of great lemonade.)
Grate the rind of two lemons and add to lemonade (optional).
Put everything into a quart jar and seal. Add 4 quarts of water (ice) when ready to serve.
Add mint leaves with a lemon slice on the side of glass as garnishment.

title: low cholesterol applesauce spice cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine wet ingredients, then add dry ingredients and mix.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Bake for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream first 6 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: okra gumbo
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Add okra and onion.
Saute until browned.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar, vinegar and water if needed.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until okra is tender.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry and combine with cheese, salad dressing mix, olives and red pepper.
Lightly grease mini-muffin tin and press 1 wrapper in each cup.
Brush with oil or spray with Pam.
Bake 5 minutes, until golden.
Remove from tins and place on baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes, until hot.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: polynesian casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Layer pineapple, ham and sweet potatoes in 2-quart casserole.
Combine brown sugar, flour, curry powder and pepper.
Blend in pineapple syrup, water and vinegar.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cover with topping before baking.

title: christmas fruit mix
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and water. Melt mixture together on stove top. Add pineapple juice and boil for 10 minutes. Remove from stove. Add egg. Return to stove and cook for 3 minutes. Remove from stove. Add lemon juice and let cool. Add Cool Whip and all fruits to mixture. Refrigerate until cool.

title: almond bark clusters
directions: Melt bark over low heat.
Add all other ingredients one at a time.
Drop onto wax paper to harden.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix together all ingredients and put in a 9 X 13 greased pan. Bake 60 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in a large airtight storage container.
To make 1 cup hot chocolate, mix 1/3 cup mixture to 1 cup hot water.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Mix marinade ingredients together in large bowl. Add veal and let stand 30 minutes. (Large zip lock bags are perfect for marinading.) Place veal on hot grill. Cook 8 minutes turning once and basing occasionally. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach, drain and squeeze out excess.
Combine spinach and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: aunt belle's brown candy
directions: Pour 1 pint sugar in skillet.
Place over low heat; brown and stir in so won't scour (takes from 20 to 30 minutes).
Put 2 pints of sugar with cream in a deep pan.
Cook until all sugar is dissolved, not stirring.
Pour burnt sugar slowly into sugar and cream until forms firm ball in cold water.
Remove from fire.
Add soda, vanilla and butter.
Set aside and let cool until lukewarm, then beat well.
Add nuts.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Slice into squares when cool.

title: easy heath bar cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions. While still warm, poke holes in cake with the handle end of a wooden spoon. Pour milk over the top of the cake. When cooled, "frost" cake with Cool Whip. Top with crumbled candy bars.

title: "sugar's" sweet potato rolls
directions: Blend together the potatoes and butter.
Dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup warm water, then add to the mashed potatoes.
Add egg, salt and sugar; blend together.
Sift flour and measure.
Add alternately with 3/4 cup warm water, stirring in each addition. Turn on well floured board and knead until smooth and elastic. Place in greased bowl and cover.
Allow to rise for 2 hours.
Shape in balls and place in greased pans.
Brush top of rolls with melted butter and let rise for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 100% parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with no-stick cooking spray. Dip chicken in spread.
Coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time:
5 minutes. Cooking time:
25 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake as directed.
Cool and fork the cake all over.
Mix sugar and milk in a pot and let it boil.
Pour cooked mixture over cake.
Take 4x sugar, after sifted, and mix with Cool Whip. Spread on cake.
Add coconut.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Melt butter in pan.
Toss in noodles. Beat eggs well, toss in cheese and then toss noodles well again. Line a (greased) pie pan or 8 x 8 inch pan with noodle mixture.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoon into hot oil where fish is frying.
Fry until brown.

title: date squares
directions: Place water, sugar and chopped dates in saucepan and boil until thick and smooth.
Cool until lukewarm.
Mix the flour, salt, oatmeal, shortening, pecans and brown sugar together to form crumbs for the crust.
Grease a brown paper bag well and line an 8-inch square pan.
Place 3/4 of the crumbs in the pan and pack down.
Add date mixture and cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares while still warm, but not hot. These are easy to mail as gifts because they don't fall apart.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Mix 3 tablespoons of melted butter and crushed Oreos.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Soften ice cream and spread on Oreos. Place in freezer.
Melt 2 bars German sweet chocolate with 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon of butter and evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil.
Stir and cool.
Spread over ice cream.
Return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with Melba rounds.

title: cathy's fresh fruit salad
directions: Slice berries.
Remove grapes from stems.
Slice bananas. Core apples, but do not peel.
Slice in bite size pieces.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice. Chop pecans.
Peel and remove orange sections from membrane.
Add lemon and pineapple juice to fruit mixture.
Add sugar to taste.
Peel and slice kiwi on top for decoration.
Chill.
Everybody loves it.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush 1/2 of Oreos.
Put in cake pan.
Mix pudding with milk. Stir in cream cheese.
Stir in Cool Whip, then spread this on top of crushed Oreos.
Then crush the rest of Oreos and put on top.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix by hand until smooth.
Put in 9 x 13-inch oiled pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: home-style macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, in 3-quart saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter; stir in flour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk, cream cheese, salt, pepper and mustard.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until sauce is thickened (3 to 4 minutes).
Stir in macaroni and cheese.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
In small bowl, stir together remaining ingredients; sprinkle over macaroni and cheese.
