Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown and heated through.

title: coffee breakers
directions: Melt margarine; stir in brown sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Spread in a large pan immediately.
Sprinkle with pecans.
In mixing bowl, dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Beat Bisquick vigorously into water.
Turn onto board dusted with Bisquick.
Knead until smooth or 20 times.
Roll into 12-inch square.
Brush with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Mix 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon; sprinkle center third of dough with half the mix.
Fold one third over center third. Sprinkle with remaining mix.
Fold over other third.
Cut crosswise into 1-inch strips.
Twist each strip.
Seal ends. Place 1 1/2 inches apart.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk (1 hour).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Invert pan.
Makes 12.

title: lemon broiled fish
directions: Combine lemon juice, butter and sage.
Pour over fish. Marinate in refrigerator at least 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Melt margarine and add to sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and mix after adding each one.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture, alternately with milk.
Add blueberries and mix gently.

title: peachy pork picante "ole"
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pork and cook to brown, stirring occasionally.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all well.
Serve with chips, or use as a vegetable dip.

title: scalloped potatoes with onions
directions: Layer in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with a lid. Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 325°. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pink salad
directions: Add jello to Cool Whip and mix well.
Then add pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts.
Chill.

title: mini cherry cheese cake
directions: Whip cream cheese with electric mixer.
Add eggs, vanilla and sugar; blend well.
Line cupcake cups with cupcake papers.
Place a vanilla wafer in each one.
Fill 2/3 full with batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cooled, spoon cherry pie filling on tops.

title: sunshine strawberry preserves
directions: Heat slowly.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Pour into Pyrex dish.
Let set in sunshine for 2 to 3 days.

title: cherry opera fudge
directions: Butter loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
In top of double boiler, melt butter in milk.
Stir in frosting mix (dry) until smooth. Heat over rapidly boiling water 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in nuts and cherries.
Spread mixture evenly in pan.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 32.

title: raspberries with banana
directions: Mash bananas until smooth; blend in lemon juice.
Add cream and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Serve over raspberries in chilled bowl.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Arrange apples in ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch. Mix baking mix, brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine until crumbly; sprinkle over apples. Bake until apples are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and let set in refrigerator until firm, but not stiff.
Then pour on top of cream cheese and crust.

title: 49er's
directions: Blend biscuit mix, sugar, eggs and pecans in a bowl; mix well. Pour mixture into a buttered 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar and serve when cooled.
(Cut into squares.)

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Heat butter and brown sugar over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar melts.
Blend in milk.
Cool.
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar until spreading consistency is reached.
Add vanilla.
Makes enough to frost two 9 x 13-inch cakes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and put into a butter 4-quart dish.
In addition to the 1/2 cup of butter, melt another 1/4 cup with 1 cup of crushed corn flakes and sprinkle on top. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy apple squares
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts. Reserve 2 cups of this crumb mixture; press remaining mixture onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan that has been greased with butter.
Combine cream cheese and milk, mixing well.
Add vanilla, egg and remaining sugar; mixing well.
Pour this mixture over crust and spread evenly.
Add chopped apples on top, spreading over mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Dry chicken and coat with flour.
Fry until brown.
Remove from skillet.
Saute shallots, garlic and green pepper until tender.
Mix in remaining ingredients (except mushrooms).
Return chicken to pan and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms; cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken to serving dish. Before pouring sauce over chicken, check to see if it is thick enough.
If not, add 1 tablespoon of flour, then pour over chicken.
Good luck.

title: low-fat sweet potato pie
directions: *If using sweet potatoes from the garden, use 1 cup of sugar or substitute Sweet 'N Low or other artificial sweetener. **Sometimes I use pumpkin pie or apple pie spice.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Cake:
Heat the oven to 350°.
Butter and flour two 9-inch cake pans.
In a large bowl, with an electric mixer set at medium-low speed, beat the room temperature butter and 1 3/4 cups of the sugar until fluffy and light in color, about 5 minutes.
Beat in 1 1/2 teaspoons of the vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
With mixer set at low speed, beat dry ingredients into butter mixture in three parts, alternating with the milk.
Pour into the prepared pans.
Bake until a toothpick stuck into the center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pans. Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: vienna sausage
directions: Stir all ingredients together and chill.
Serves 8.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Take the bone out of the salmon and take the skin off; flake salmon.
In a 2-quart casserole, sprayed with Pam, put a layer of crackers, then a layer of salmon.
Dot with butter; repeat until all salmon and crackers are used.
Dot with butter and put enough milk in to cover.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese and melt over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve while hot or warm.

title: chicken a la swiss
directions: Layer ingredients in greased 9 x 13-inch dish as follows: chicken, cheese, soup, water, stuffing and oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients (except marshmallows) and mix well by hand.
Pour into ovenproof casserole dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Cover.
Bake until marshmallows turn light colored.
Serve hot.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Melt margarine in large frying pan and lightly brown chicken pieces.
Remove chicken pieces; add onions and cook slowly until limp and yellow.
Sprinkle with paprika; add chicken pieces, salt and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: apricot surprise
directions: Boil together apricot jello and pineapple.
Cool!
Cream together apricot baby food and cream cheese.
To this, fold in Cool Whip.
Add mixtures together and chill overnight.
To serve, cut into squares.

title: my favorite meat loaf
directions: Crush crackers into crumbs.
Add to ground beef.
Add chopped onion, salt, pepper and eggs.
Stir until well mixed.
Add milk. Bake at 350° in oven for 45 minutes or until done.
If you add 1 cup of milk instead of 1/2 cup, you can bake in microwave oven. Make into 2 loaves for micro and bake in a Pyrex baking dish.
Set dish on Pyrex pie plate to cook.
This keeps meat loaf from getting tough in bottom.
Takes 15 to 17 minutes in micro.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Cut lemon in half; remove seeds. Cut into very thin slices. In a large saucepan, bring water, lemon slices, and oregano to a boil. Add whole mushrooms, place a heatproof plate on top to keep mushrooms from floating to the top, and cook for 5-6 minutes, until mushrooms turn white. Drain.

title: my favorite bread pudding
directions: Butter bread and cut in 1-inch squares.
Place in lightly greased 7 1/2 x 11 3/4-inch baking pan.

title: double pie crusts
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add water and form dough into 2 balls.
Roll out on floured surface in circle.
Place in pie tin and fill with favorite fruit filling.
Place second crust on top of filling. Bake at 350° until brown, about 35 minutes.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, sugar and sour cream.
Add 4 eggs and beat well.
Pour half batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans and sprinkle over batter.
Add rest of batter and run knife through to marbleize.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini pie
directions: To prepare squash, peel, scoop out the center and slice like apples.
Cover with cold water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in the 2-crust pie shell at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill crock-pot heaping full of apples (lid may not fit down at first, but apples shrink).
Drizzle sugar, spices and salt over apples (sweet apples require less sugar).
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.
Lower heat and cook all day.

title: company potato casserole
directions: Mix together soup, sour cream, curry and pepper.
Put half of mixture in small baking dish.
Add potatoes.
Add remaining soup mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Add cheese and more bread crumbs.
Heat 10 or 15 minutes in oven.
Boiled eggs sliced over top are good and look pretty.

title: lori's potatoes
directions: Melt butter in nonstick skillet; saute onions in butter until transparent.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz and melt slowly.
Put hash browns in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp and crab meat casserole
directions: Saute seasoning in oleo, blend with rice, soups, shrimp and crab meat.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut dip and apples
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender, except apples.
Dip apples in peanut dip.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Boil raisins until soft.
Drain and cool.
Combine oil, eggs, water and sugar.
Sift flour, salt, nutmeg, soda and cinnamon. Make a well in the center.
Add pumpkin and blend until moistened. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Turn into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with cream cheese.

title: ezra's homemade ice cream(one gallon)
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Add milk and mix together well. Put in container for ice cream freezer.
Start churn with ice and ice cream salt.
When mixture gets slightly thickened, add fruit. Continue churning until hardened.

title: peasant minestrone(minestrone rustica)
directions: Put
all
the
vegetables in a large saucepan with beef ribs, salt,
pepper and boiling water.
Cover and cook over a low heat for
about
1/2 hours.
Remove meat from bone and return
to soup.
Add
sausage and cook for another 1/2 hour. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: breakfast cream cheese pastry
directions: Layer 1 can of rolls in a large baking pan. Cream the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Pour over rolls in pan.
Top with the other can of crescent rolls. Brush top with beaten egg white and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Stir the first three ingredients together in heavy saucepan. Cook to soft ball stage (236 degrees).
Add the rest of ingredients, mixing well. Pour into buttered 9x13 pan.

title: eloise's yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt,
Crisco
and eggs together.
Boil milk and let cool.
Mix yeast with warm water and add to milk.
Mix flour with milk, yeast
mixture,
then
add sugar and egg mixture. Knead.
Place in warm place to rise until double, about 2 hours. Knead down.
Place
in greased bowl.
Will keep well in refrigerator for several
days.
When
ready to bake, pinch off dough and roll into balls.
Put
in
greased
pan
and let rise several hours or until double in size.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: frozen fruit salad no. 2
directions: Thoroughly
blend
cream
cheese, sugar and mayonnaise. Fold in	the
fruit
cocktail,
nuts,
marshmallows and frozen topping. Freeze in fruit can.
You can cut the bottom off and slide through to slice.
May be tinted any color.

title: relish for hot dogs
directions: Mix and serve on hot dog.

title: apple bars
directions: Combine the 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt; cut in butter or margarine until crumbs are the size of small peas.
Stir in egg yolks.
Divide mixture in half.
Press one half over bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine apples, the remaining sugar and flour and cinnamon; arrange over bottom crust.
Crumble remaining dough over apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Drizzle with thin powdered sugar icing, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Makes approximately 20 bars.

title: french fried sweet potatoes
directions: You will need a deep fryer.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Melt butter, add onions and celery and cook over low heat until transparent.
Add flour and mix well.
Add milk and seasoning; mix well.
Add crabmeat.
Pour into buttered dish. Crumble crackers over crabmeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken chipotle corn soup
directions: In a 3-4 quart pan, cook onions and garlic in a little oil. Add chilies, cumin, corn and broth.
Bring to a boil, cover, and cook about 15 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Ladle into bowls and add lime juice, cilantro and cream cheese cubes.

title: country-style barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in roaster, fat side up.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Drain off all grease.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat to boiling point.
Pour sauce over ribs and cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours, basting occasionally. Serves 4 to 6.

title: scones
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Knead 10 times on Bisquick-covered board.
Shape into one large or 2 small flattened rounds.
Moisten tops with small amount of milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Cut each round into 6 pie shaped wedges and place on baking sheet.
Bake until golden brown.
Makes 6 large or 12 small scones.

title: potato salad
directions: Hard-boil the eggs, boil the potatoes for about 20 minutes. When cool, cut potatoes in cubes.
Cut eggs in small cubes.
Add mayonnaise, as much as desired.
Add salt and pepper; mix.

title: nana's banana bread
directions: Beat butter; add sugars. Add egg and egg whites and vanilla; beat until well blended. Add bananas; beat 30 seconds. Combine flour, baking soda, powder and salt. Add alternately with cream to banana mixture, ending with flour. Add nuts to batter. Bake in greased on bottom only loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: ashley boone's asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, cheese and chips; repeat layers.
Cook at 350° until light brown.

title: skillet potatoes
directions: In frying pan, cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Stir in soup and pepper; gradually blend in milk. Add potatoes.
Heat; stir now and then.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Melt butter; place in 9 x 13-inch pan (spray with Pam first).
Bake at 350° in oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: nice rice pudding
directions: Combine milk and eggs.
Add cooked rice, raisins, sugar, salt, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put this dish in a pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients (batter will be real thick).
In a separate bowl mix eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and nuts.
Blend together with zucchini.
Put in two greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Baking times varies for different ovens.

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Mix, roll out thin and cut like biscuits. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes on lightly greased pan.

title: mustard dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill 2 to 3 hours. Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add onions to drippings and cook until tender.
Add ground beef and brown.
Stir in chopped tomatoes, chopped green pepper, chili sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir in uncooked noodles.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir frequently.
Stir in bacon.

title: georgia pecan cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Gradually add orange juice, floured raisins and pecans. Mix until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 275 degrees for 2 hours.

title: aunt wilma's zucchini squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onion, green pepper, and red pepper. Add salt and let stand for 1 hour. Drain and add vinegar, sugar, pepper, mustard seed and turmeric. Bring to boil and cook 10 minutes. Stir occasionally while cooking. Put into jars and seal. Cold pack about 10 minutes. Makes about 8 pints.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, celery salt and dill (optional).
Add this mixture to cucumbers.
Drain by hand and put into jars.
Cover.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Beat well. Add melted chocolate and mix. Add dry ingredients, alternately with sour milk. Grease cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill well before serving.
Chopped onion and cucumbers may be added if you so desire.

title: pie dough
directions: If you use self-rising flour, leave the salt and soda out, but if plain flour, add salt and soda to flour and mix well.
Add shortening to flour; cut in shortening with knife or fork.
(I use my hand; it is faster.)
When you get the shortening and flour like meal, you then add water (cold, if plain flour; hot, if self-rising).
Add water to get it to your desired stiffness.
Use all the flour you need to knead it to where you can cut them out or roll it out.
Put dough in refrigerator and chill.
It rolls out better.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Add all ingredients, except buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot curry beef(serves 8)
directions: Wipe beef well.
Mix flour and curry powder.
Coat meat cubes with flour mixture.
Place meat in crock-pot.
Add garlic, raisins, sliced apples and pepper.
Mix together Lipton onion soup mix and water; pour over meat and other ingredients in crock-pot. Stir to blend.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours or until meat is tender.
Before serving, add additional curry powder to taste (up to 1 tablespoon).
Serve over cooked rice or egg noodles.
Serves 8 people.

title: monkey bread
directions: Lightly grease a Bundt pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Remove biscuits from can and separate.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Dip into butter; then put into bag with sugar mixture.
Close bag and shake to coat biscuit.
Put biscuit pieces into Bundt pan.
Repeat.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, until browned at 375°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat well, stirring to keep it crumbly.
Pour off fat from skillet.
Add water,
taco
sauce
and
garlic
salt. Cook slowly 20 minutes.
Meanwhile,
combine
chilled lettuce, onion, tomatoes and cheese in
salad bowl and toss well.
Just before serving, mix in corn
chips;
add
meat
sauce and toss again. Sprinkle top generously
with
grated Parmesan cheese. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fiesta tamale pie
directions: Saute onion and garlic until onion is yellow in the butter and oil.
Add beef and sausage and cook until brown.
Add tomatoes, corn, salt and chili powder; simmer 20 minutes.
Pour into 11 x 7-inch oblong baking dish.
Press olives into mixture.
Mix cornmeal, milk and eggs; spread over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Drain sauerkraut in colander until liquid disappears, then squeeze and dry.
Mix with rest of the ingredients and let stand 48 hours.
Can be kept in any covered container or quart jar. Lasts for weeks when kept refrigerated.
Very good.

title: goulash
directions: Fry bacon; drain on paper towel.
Fry 1 onion (diced) and 1 pound hamburger in bacon grease until browned.
Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook macaroni about 10 minutes.
Add spaghetti and tomato sauce and hamburger.
Mix all together; crumble bacon on top.
Simmer in electric skillet.

title: "more"(main dish)
directions: Cook macaroni, rinse and drain.
Brown meat with peppers, onions and mushrooms, adding olives when done.
Drain excess fat. Add all to macaroni with tomato paste and 1 can water plus cheese. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Bake 2 hours at 300°, covered.
Uncover last half hour.

title: lavender salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add juice from cherries until lavender color.
Prepare dream whip according to package directions, add to cream cheese, mix well.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain well. Mix egg, mayonnaise, soup, onion and cheese together.
Stir in broccoli; put in a 2-quart casserole.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with 10 to 15 crumbled Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: sister myrtle ragon homemade rolls
directions: Mix yeast and lukewarm water; set aside.
Add shortening to mashed potatoes while hot.
Add sugar, salt, beaten eggs and potato water.
Add yeast.
Add flour, 2 cups at a time, beating well.
The last 2 cups will likely have to be kneaded in.

title: three cheese casserole
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper until brown.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Prepare noodles as directed on package; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread half of noodles in 11 x 7-inch glass casserole dish.
Top with meat sauce.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Repeat layer and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, salt, spices, egg yolks, flour and cornstarch.
Scald milk and add to mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gently fold mixture into beaten egg whites.
Pour into 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until silver knife blade inserted into center of filling comes out clean.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients, except tortillas, in large bowl.
Add ground beef to soup mixture.
Layer mixture with tortillas in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes, until bubbly, at 350°.
May serve with tortilla chips.
Good with Spanish rice.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cover bread with milk for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, melted butter, salt and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.
Set pan in pan of water and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Way bars in double boiler over medium heat.
Use 1/2 Eagle Brand milk to help melt candy bars.
After melting, mix all ingredients.
Fill ice cream freezer with all ingredients.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes casserole
directions: How much potatoes and ham
depend
on
how big you want your casserole to be.

title: bird nests(swedish)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolk.
Stir in flour.
Form into balls and dip into slightly beaten egg white.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven. Press centers and return to oven for 10 minutes.
When cool, fill centers with jam.

title: cheesy bacon and ham casserole
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove and drain on paper towel, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook ham in reserved drippings in skillet over medium heat until browned.
Cook grits according to package directions.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese and butter until melted.
Stir in bacon, ham, eggs and remaining ingredients. Pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: georgia burgers
directions: Mix ground beef with pecans, onion, salt, cloves and 3 tablespoons peaches.
Shape into 4 patties about 1-inch thick. Broil 4 inches from heat for 6 minutes.
While meat is cooking, season remaining peaches with brown sugar, vinegar and ginger. Brush over patties while hot.
Turn and brush again.
Broil 6 minutes longer for medium or more for well done.

title: oven chicken kiev
directions: Mix butter, parsley (1 tablespoon) and garlic powder.
Shape into rectangle (3 x 2-inches).
Cover and freeze about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken soft tacos
directions: Bake chicken at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut up into 1/2-inch cubes.
Saute chicken with minced garlic in a large skillet. Serve on soft wraps.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients but jello and berries.
Bring to boil and cook until glaze is clear.
Add jello and food coloring. Combine berries and glaze.
Put in baked pie shell, using pie crust recipe in this section for strawberry pie.
Chill.

title: lasagna supreme
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package.
Drain, chill in cold water for 5 minutes and re-drain.
In large baking pan, layer 1/4 meat sauce (spaghetti sauce), 1/3 of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and Parmesan ending with meat sauce and Parmesan.
Cover with foil and bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes before serving. Yields 12 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour pan.
In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; add carrots, oil and eggs.
Mix until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool before adding frosting.

title: authentic mexican meringues
directions: Add salt and vanilla to the egg whites and beat until mixture stands in peaks.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until very stiff.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto a well-buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Combine 1 cup of rice and 2 cups of water; cook rice and add and mix together beef, onion, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Top with mushrooms or combine with other ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Beat together with a fork the egg white and water in large bowl.
Add walnuts and toss to coat all pieces.
In a small bowl combine all dry ingredients and sprinkle over walnuts.
Spread nuts on greased cookie sheet.
Bake uncovered in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove and put on waxed paper to cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine Jell-O, cornstarch and sugar.
Mix well.
Add water. Stir.
Bring to boil.
Continue cooking and stirring until clear. Let cool.
Put strawberries in pie shell.
Pour on glaze and put into refrigerator until served.

title: pecan tassies
directions: You will need 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.

title: slovak haluski
directions: Grate potatoes; add salt, eggs and flour and mix well.
If dough is too stiff, add a little water, 1/4 cup or more.
Drop small portions from tip of spoon into boiling water.
Cook 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Serve with cottage cheese or fried cabbage.

title: rich hot chocolate
directions: Combine chocolate, syrup and water in saucepan; heat until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Refrigerate until cool. Add vanilla.
Beat cream until stiff.
Gradually beat in chocolate mixture.
Beat until mixture mounds in bowl.
Spoon chocolate mixture into a cup.
Fill cup with hot milk.
Stir.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat.
Drain fat, if any.
Add all ingredients.
Cook at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: corn meal chess pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, beating in well, one at a time. Add flour, corn meal, vanilla and lemon extract.
Beat well.
Pour into an 8-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° until firm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350 for 55-60 minutes.
Cool and ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: raisin and nut sandwich spread
directions: Grind raisins in food chopper; mix with salad dressing.
When thin enough, add chopped nuts.

title: turkey and sausage hash
directions: Brown sausage as directed on package.
Add butter, onion and green pepper and cook about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, then milk. Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add turkey, parsley, seasonings and bread cubes.
Cook over very low heat about 25 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: frozen cranberry dessert
directions: Combine and spread in casserole. Freeze until firm (at least 4 hours). Best if prepared day before.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook and peel beets.
When you can stick a fork into beet easily, it is done.
After peeled, slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Set aside.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo, shortening and sugar well.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk, in which soda has been dissolved.
Add vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add coconut and nuts.
Bake in three 9-inch layers in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla.
Mix in slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over top. Bake in 350° oven approximately 45 minutes.

title: meat-spaghetti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Brown and drain sausage.
Add chopped vegetables.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, oregano, salt, sugar and 1 cup water.
Simmer for 30 minutes; covered.

title: holiday punch(guatemala)
directions: Add sugar to pot of water (use as much water as desired for punch) Add cinnamon sticks and boil.
Taste at intervals to ensure water has a sweet flavor, add sugar as needed.
Simmer until cinnamon scent is apparent.
Add dried fruit and pineapple.
Simmer for a few minutes until fruit softens up.
Serve piping hot.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits.
Put some of the chopped apple on each biscuit.
Fold and seal biscuit with apple pieces inside.
Put in a 2-quart baking dish.
Melt butter and pour over biscuits.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Drain hominy and add to the first mixture.
Fold in crushed Fritos.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add blueberries and pineapple.
Let gel in glass bowl.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla with electric mixer
until smooth consistency.
Spread over gelled Jell-O.
Sprinkle with crushed walnuts.

title: mexican seasoning mix for chili or tacos
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and store in tightly covered container.
Use 3 tablespoons with 1/2 cup water to every pound of meat.
Use for chili or tacos.

title: green beans with almonds
directions: In a large pan, combine beans, bouillon cubes, water, oil and onions.
Bring to a boil on the stove and cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add almonds during last 15 minutes of cooking or use almonds as a garnish when served.
Yield:
8 to 12 servings.

title: baked stuffed fish(any type fish may be used)
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
If whole fish, rub cavity with lemon juice.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package; drain.
Stir in margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into 2 buttered 10-inch pie plates.
Spread cottage cheese equally over spaghetti.
In skillet, brown hamburg and onion.
Stir in rest of the ingredients.
Turn meat mixture into spaghetti crusts.
Bake, uncovered, and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cornmeal scrapple
directions: In saucepan, combine the cornmeal, milk, salt and sugar. Gradually stir in water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Cook covered for 10 minutes longer or until very thick, stirring occasionally.
Remove from the heat and stir in sausage.
Pour into a greased 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan (the pan will be very full).
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: better than ?  ?  ?  chocolate cake
directions: Prepare chocolate cake according to package directions.
Bake and cool completely. When cool, poke 16 to 20 holes in cake with rounded end of wooden spoon. Spread the top of the cake with the ice cream topping.
Pour 1 can of sweetened condensed milk over ice cream topping. Chill overnight. Frost with Cool Whip. Garnish with Heath bars that have been broken into tiny pieces.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together margarine, powdered sugar and crackers.
Use an oblong dish or pan and press cracker crumbs in the bottom.
Be sure to save some for the top of the filling.
Beat evaporated milk chilled until stiff.
Mix together lemon jello and water, then mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Combine the two mixtures together and beat well.
Add filling to cracker crust and top with remaining crackers.
Chill and store in refrigerator.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and let jell.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring carrots with water to cover to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Mix all other ingredients, then add carrots.
Cover tightly and chill overnight.
(Any marinade leftover may be refrigerated and used as a dressing for salad.)

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Mix in 8-inch glass cake dish the rhubarb, white sugar and water.
In another bowl, mix brown sugar, flour and butter until crumbly, then spread over top of rhubarb. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together and pour into 8-inch square pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break veggies into bite size pieces; add carrots, mix mayonnaise, onion, sugar and vinegar to taste.
Add bacon, raisins, and nuts to veggies.
Toss with dressing.

title: spaghetti ala carbonara
directions: In a large pot, bring water to a boil and cook pasta according to directions.
In a frying pan, cook bacon and drain, then cook Prosciutto ham and drain.
Crumble bacon and Prosciutto.
Chop parsley.
Reserve two tablespoons of oil and cook onion and garlic cloves until transparent.

title: cherry glazed pork loin roast
directions: Place roast on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer so bulb is in center of thickest part of meat.
Roast, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat thermometer registers 170° (allow about 30 to 35 minutes per pound).

title: paella(rice with veggies and meat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use an ovenproof dish or saucepan.
Cook chicken first in oil.
Boil broth in saucepan.
In pan used for chicken, brown onion and pimientos; add rice and toss to coat.
Add spices and broth to rice mixture.
Place chicken and vegetables on top.
Do not stir!
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, milk and vanilla. Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked crust.
Bake about 1 hour at 300°.

title: amish pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Mix together and bake in a sheet pan at 350°.
Beat together pudding mix and milk.
Crumble cake into pudding mix, cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: chicken livers
directions: Chop shallots in skillet.
Saute in the oil until tender. Dredge livers in flour.
Place over shallots until brown.
Cover with orange juice.
Cover and simmer until livers are tender.

title: stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onions; pour off fat.
Add bread crumbs, egg and seasonings, mix well.
Stir in soup, sour cream and water.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cooked noodles and cook another 15 minutes.

title: holiday ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine fruit, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Arrange sauerkraut in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Layer corned beef and cheese over sauerkraut.
Mix mayonnaise and Thousand Island dressing.
Spread over cheese.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Melt shortening in a large skillet.
Cook and stir meat and onion in shortening until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Add water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 50 minutes.

title: nick's knack stew
directions: Place ingredients into saucepan and simmer for 9 hours, 31 minutes and 27 seconds.
If you have the knack, you will also have some wonderful stew, if not, you will wonder what it is you have.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover vegetables with water.
Cook until tender, about 25 minutes.
Put in soup, sour cream and cheese.
Heat a few minutes, then add milk and serve.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: sauce for meat balls
directions: Mix ketchup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meat balls already cooked.
Heat.

title: shrimp and linguini delight
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add shrimp; cook 3 to 5 minutes. Drain well; rinse with cold water.
Chill.
Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.

title: bacon crackers
directions: Mix mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in cheese and bacon.
Spoon 1/2 tablespoon mixture over each cracker.
Arrange 8 or 9 crackers at a time in a circle on a plate.
Microwave, uncovered, on High (100%) until hot and puffed, about 30 seconds.

title: hawaiian ham and rice casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine honey, oleo, soy sauce and green pepper.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly. Turn into a greased casserole (I use Pam), 2 quarts or larger. Bake covered for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Can be frozen and reheated in microwave or oven.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small flowerets.
Dice onion and tomato. Drain and add kidney beans.
Add cheese.
Toss together with salad dressing.
Set at least 1 hour.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: You will also need an 8-inch spring-form pan.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix ingredients in small mixing bowl.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: leftover roast casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in butter.
Blend soup, milk, 3/4 cup cheese and pepper.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole alternate layers (starting with potatoes).
Sprinkle top with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls out flat on cookie sheet. Pinch together to make a solid base. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: party punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl.
Raspberry is great!

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and add eggs.
Beat together and add evaporated milk, vanilla and oleo.
Stir together until mixed. Spread flour in bottom of frozen crust and sprinkle sugar over the flour.
Mix this around on the crust.
Pour in the filling and bake for about 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cashew bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix cookie mix, egg, butter or margarine, baking powder and vanilla until smooth.
Spread dough in greased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle cashews over dough.
Press lightly onto surface.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars (2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Makes 2 dozen bars.

title: sole florentine au gratin
directions: Spread spinach in 6 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with Swiss cheese, then American cheese.
Cover cheese with sole fillets. Last, cover sole with cream of Cheddar soup.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve with long grain and wild rice.
Serves 6.

title: sherried mushroom soup
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the lemon slices, in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 2 to 4 minutes, until hot but not boiling.
To serve:
Pour the soup into 4 serving bowls and top each one with a lemon slice.

title: easy as pie apple cake
directions: Place apples in a 9-inch pie shell.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Sprinkle all but 2 teaspoons of cinnamon sugar mixture on top of apples.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk until thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers over pudding.
Pour rest of pudding mixture over 2nd layer of crackers.
Frost the rest of graham crackers with icing and place on top.

title: very special brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
Mix ingredients together until well-blended.
Pour into pan and spread evenly.
Bake approximately 20 minutes or until top is golden. Cool thoroughly before slicing.
When cool, sprinkle top with 10x sugar.
Recipe may be doubled and frozen.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Remove seed and vein from peppers and chop fine in blender. Mix all ingredients except pectin and coloring.
Cook on low heat 45 minutes, then bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from stove and let stand 5 minutes.
Add pectin and coloring.
Pour into jelly jars and let cool to gel.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend in blender 30 seconds.
Pour into greased and floured deep 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Add drained beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: molded cheese salad
directions: Prepare jello in usual way.
Chill until it begins to thicken. Whip lightly until fluffy and fold in all ingredients.
Pour into mold or long shallow pan or large bowl.
Serves 12.

title: cayenne cheese cookies
directions: Melt butter; add other ingredients.
Form 2 log rolls.
Chill approximately 4 hours.
Slice and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together confectioners sugar, coconut, peanut butter, margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Form into 1-inch balls and put in refrigerator for 10 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Grease tube pan lightly.
Preheat to 350°.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add sugar, then eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir, but do not beat or use mixer.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat with hands into a 9 x 13-inch pan, lightly greased.
Mix the remaining ingredients. Pour over other mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° (325° if glass baking dish).
Don't cut until completely cool.

title: mississippi rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This makes 6 generous servings.

title: blintz bubble ring
directions: Cut cream cheese into 20 pieces; roll into balls.
Roll out each biscuit in 3-inch circle.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Place 1 cheese ball and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixture in each biscuit circle.
Pinch dough to seal.
Pour half of melted butter into bottom of 8 or 10-inch ring mold or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle the nuts and half of the remaining cinnamon mixture into pan.
Place the rolls close together around bottom of pan, seam sides up. Sprinkle rest of butter and cinnamon mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes until browned.
Cool 5 minutes and invert on a serving platter.
Serve warm.
Can be refrigerated and reheated in foil.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions with sugar in the butter until tender.
Add broth and water.
Cover and simmer gently for 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in individual bowls.
Top with toasted slice of French bread.
Sprinkle cheeses over the tops of bread.
Place bowl under broiler until lightly browned.
Serve and enjoy a salad along side.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and place in loaf pan. Cook at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Pour off liquid 2 or 3 times. Spread ketchup on top.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate. Add salsa to cover cream cheese. Add peppers, then cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs; add dry ingredients.
Add mustard, vinegar and milk.
Cook in double boiler until boiling.
Remove from heat. When cool, add salad dressing.
Pour over prepared potatoes, celery and onion for delicious potato salad.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, eggs and water; beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Add orange extract.
Stir in oats.
Drop by slightly rounded tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes. Yield: 5 dozen.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix together.
Mix 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to 1 cup of hot water for 1 cup of tea.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Layer carrots and onion in casserole dish.
Melt cheese and butter; pour over carrots.
Crush Ritz crackers and put on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, salt, oil, soda and cinnamon. Mix well and add baby food.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost when cool.

title: dilled carrots
directions: Clean and cut carrots; boil until tender approximately 5 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Rinse in cold water.
Let cool to room temperature.
In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, then pour over carrots.
Best results if made the night before serving, allowing to sit.
Stir before serving.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar; add 2 eggs, one at a time.
Then add water or berry juice.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and spices together.
Add to batter.
Coat berries with flour.
Fold into batter.
This will keep berries from sinking to bottom.
Grease and flour two or three 8 or 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° until done. Frost with seven minute frosting or your favorite (caramel is very good).

title: seven seas casserole
directions: In a saucepan, combine soup, water, salt, onion and pepper. Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour half of mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Make 3 layers in casserole using Minute rice (right from the box), then peas and then tuna.
Add remaining soup mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 or 25 minutes, cutting through mixture with a knife after baking 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Shake mixture with potatoes in large bag.
Potatoes can be peeled or unpeeled and quartered.
Place in a large baking dish. Dot with margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: spareribs and kraut
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ribs, in a large casserole or baking dish.
Put ribs, which have been cooked ahead of time, into the kraut mixture.
Cover with a casserole lid or foil.
Cook at 325° for about 2 hours.

title: big ma's pound cake
directions: Blend margarine and Crisco until creamy.
Add sugar gradually and continue creaming.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add lemon and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: or-an-gey tapioca
directions: Cook packages of tapioca pudding with only 3 cups liquid. Drain juice from oranges and pineapple and add enough water to make 3 cups.
Cool.
Add oranges, pineapple and the Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
This keeps for days.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and mace together.
Add alternately flour and milk, mixing well.
Fold in blueberries.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer Doritos, chicken and onion in a large baking dish.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel and broth and pour over layered mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together (cover with bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons oleo).
Make up and refrigerate overnight and set out 1 hour before cooking.
Cook for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Blend bananas in blender.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add bananas and flour mixture to mix.
Put into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: christmas punch
directions: Makes approximately 7 quarts.
Will serve 30 to 35 people.

title: easy spaghetti skillet
directions: In a large skillet, cook 1 pound of ground beef until it loses its red color, breaking up with spoon as it cooks.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, garlic powder, tomatoes and soup.
Stir in 1/2 pound cooked, drained spaghetti.
Sprinkle all with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Cover and heat 10 to 15 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pea soup
directions: Rinse and sort peas.
Soak in 2 quarts water for overnight.
In the morning, drain.
Add all of the other ingredients except for diced ham into a large stockpot.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 2 hours.
Add the diced ham for the last half hour of cooking.
This soup thickens if allowed to sit overnight, so it can be extended by thinning it with water and still have a hearty soup.

title: fruit pie
directions: Beat together in a medium bowl the butter and sugars until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine salt, flour and baking powder in another bowl.
Add dry mix to butter mix gradually.
Mix until moistened.

title: overnight snowdrop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: 1-2-3 puffs
directions: Mix all the ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 325° until slightly brown.

title: ma wilson's vanilla wafer cake
directions: Melt oleo.
Roll vanilla wafers until crumbled finely. Combine oleo, eggs, sugar, coconut, milk and pecans.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 275° for 1 1/2 or 2 hours.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Combine coconut and pecans.
Line bottom of pan with this.
Make cake according to package directions.
Pour over mixture. Soften margarine and cream cheese.
Mix with sugar and pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook dates, sugar and margarine, stirring until margarine is well absorbed (boiling a few minutes).
Remove from heat; add nuts and cereal.
Cool.
Shape into balls, then coat with powdered sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spread ketchup on top while baking. Yields 6 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring and cocoa.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and color mixture.
Beat for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup buttermilk.
Slowly add flour, salt and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed.
Mix soda in small amount of water and fold into batter.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli with onion.
Cook as directed on broccoli package.
Drain.
Combine vegetables with remaining ingredients. Pour into greased, shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new salem corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except half of Cheddar cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Put other half of Cheddar cheese on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: amaretto mushrooms
directions: In a saute pan, heat the clarified butter.
Cut the stems and wash the mushrooms; pat them dry.
Saute the mushrooms in the butter with the lemon juice added.
Just as the mushrooms are done, add the Amaretto and let simmer for about 30 seconds.
The butter and Amaretto will make a glaze.
Put the mushrooms in a small serving dish (a Welsh Rarebit dish works great); pour the glaze over them.
Garnish with a sprig of fresh parsley at each end of dish.
Serves 2.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Beat at moderate speed 3-5 minutes. Stir in chocolate bits.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch bundt or tube pan at 350° for 50 - 60 minutes.

title: dunka(german pancakes)
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls on hot griddle.
Cook until done.
Serve hot with jelly, syrup, honey or powdered sugar.

title: chicken potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except beets together. Blend thoroughly. Fold in the beets.
Serve cold on a bed of lettuce. Garnish with chopped eggs and parsley.

title: queen cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Mix well. Add all dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until tested done.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In medium saucepan bring water to a boil.
Stir in soup mix. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
With a fork, quickly stir in the egg, a little at a time, until it congeals.
Serve with chow mein noodles or crispy Chinese fried noodles.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thaw shrimp; pat dry with paper towels and chop coarsely; set aside.
Place tomatoes and green chilies in a colander; press and drain well.
Using electric mixer or food processor, blend all ingredients except shrimp.
Add shrimp and stir in by hand, briefly and gently to retain chunk texture.
Chill 4 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook dinner following directions on package.
Mix together with all ingredients.
Toss well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Chill thoroughly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: crabmeat supreme
directions: Unwrap cheese.
Place in a 3-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until cheese is softened.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: marinated veggies
directions: Mix together.
Let sit until chilled before serving.

title: gert's blueberry muffins
directions: Whisk egg by hand until well beaten.
Add the milk and oil. Add dry ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Add blueberries.
Put in paper baking cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: egg salad plus
directions: Coarsely chop the 5 eggs and put into a medium size bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
The mayonnaise can be increased up to 3 1/2 tablespoons if a thinner egg salad is preferred.

title: southwest chicken
directions: Bake boneless chicken for 1 hour at 350°. Drain juice and pour picante sauce over chicken breast. Then top with cheese and put lid on and place in oven to melt cheese.

title: s'more cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined flour and crumbs; mix well.
Press onto bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes, or until golden brown.
Spread chocolate over crust.
Top with marshmallows.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes, or until marshmallows are lightly browned.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins and cook until done, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Let potatoes cool off by draining water off and set aside.
Should take about 1 hour to cool.
Remove skins from potatoes and cube them.
In a big bowl combine the potatoes and the other ingredients.

title: 1-2-3-4 freezer jam
directions: Place fruit and sugar in a kettle and cook until mixture starts to thicken; take off fire and add three small packages orange jello.
Put in jars and freeze.

title: no sugar apple pie
directions: Thaw apple juice.
Add tapioca.
Heat so juice thickens a little.
Add salt, cinnamon and sliced apples.
Mix.
Put in crust and dot with margarine.
Cover with another crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: rice dish
directions: Combine all ingredients in uncovered casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spray large casserole dish with no-stick spray.
Mix soup, rice, celery and milk in baking dish.
Layer chicken breasts (skin side up) on top of mixture.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 1/2 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, orange and peeling, pineapple, celery and English walnuts.

title: service man special
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Stir in jar of marshmallow cream, 3 cups crushed graham crackers and vanilla. Pour in greased pan to cool.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Mix eggs and milk. Add all together until smooth.
Add shortening.
Bake on hot griddle.
Serve with butter and syrup.
Makes 18.

title: hot dog soup
directions: Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Heat soup according to directions.
Add other ingredients.
Heat until thoroughly warm.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat the fat.
Brown the pork chops on both sides.
Pour off drippings.
Pour around the chops a mixture of soup, milk and water.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes, until chops are tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: 5 bean bake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, saving garden peas for last. Pour into a large baking dish and bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Good for large groups.

title: fire and ice pickles
directions: Cut pickles into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Combine pickle slices, sugar, hot sauce and red pepper in large bowl; stir well. Cover mixture and let stand 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Spoon mixture into 3 (1 pint) jars; add 1 garlic clove to each jar. Cover and refrigerate up to 1 month.
For best flavor, wait 1 week before eating.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish with a lid.
Place in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Stir 1/2 way through baking.
Margarine can be decreased, if desired.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Spread broccoli, onion and cheese evenly over bottom of pie plate. Place remaining ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: chocolate cake(no eggs)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add to melted butter, water, vanilla and vinegar.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: steak
directions: Let the steak rest outside the refrigerator for 1 hour before cooking.
Use a hot, clean oiled grill.
If pan roasting, preheat the oven to 450°.
Liberally season the steak with the salt and pepper and press the seasoning into the meat.
Grill the steaks for about 5 to 6 minutes on each side for medium rare.
The fillet will cook a little faster than the strip loin.
Move the steaks every 2 minutes or so for even cooking and a crispy exterior.
For pan roasting, heat a cast iron skillet with a little olive oil until smoking hot.
Turn on the fan, open the window and stand back to avoid getting splattered!
Using tongs, place the steaks in the center of the pan.
Cook until the first side is seared brown, about 4 minutes.
Turn the steaks and place the pan in the oven until the steaks are done, about 6 minutes for medium rare. Remove the steaks to a carving board and let rest for at least 5 minutes before carving.

title: nine-day cole slaw
directions: In large bowl, cut cabbage, onions and pepper.
Put 2 cups of sugar over and mix well; set aside.
In small saucepan, mix oil, vinegar, salt, celery seed and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Bring mixture to boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and pimentos.
Stir and let cool.
Refrigerate and cover.
Will keep 9 days or longer.

title: rhubarb-strawberry deep-dish pie
directions: Thaw strawberries enough to break apart.
Heat oven to 400°. Butter an 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Combine rhubarb, strawberries and lemon rind lightly in large bowl.
Sprinkle in lemon juice.
Combine sugar and tapioca and toss lightly through the fruit.
Put in prepared baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Roll pastry in a square larger than baking dish.
Lay it over the fruit; turn in edges and crimp and seal.
Cut vents in top.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar, milk, syrup, chocolate and shortening in saucepan. Let come to boil, scraping sides until well dissolved.
Boil 3 minutes or 220° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat until spreading consistency.
(Can be thinned with milk or cream if allowed to get too thick.)
Will ice 2 (9-inch) layers 1 1/2 times.
Will ice 3 (9-inch) layers.
Creamy and good.

title: glazed strawberry tart
directions: Stir together flour, almonds, sugar, lemon rind and salt in a large bowl.
Cut butter into flour mixture with a pastry blender or 2 knifes, until coarse crumbs form.
Whisk together egg and vanilla in a small bowl; stir into flour mixture until a dough forms.
Shape into a disk.
Wrap in plastic; refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: raised donuts
directions: Measure 1/2 cup warm water into a mixing bowl.
Add, stirring until dissolved, yeast.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix with a spoon until smooth.
Add enough flour to handle easily.
Mix with hand.

title: happy hour mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine, brush over mushroom caps, coating thoroughly.
Stir together remaining margarine, garlic and cheese until well blended.
Stir in wine, soy and crumbs until well blended.
Place mushrooms cavity side up, on a large rimmed baking dish.
Evenly mound filling in each mushroom.
Broil about 6 inches below broiler until bubbly and lightly browned (about 3 minutes).
Serve warm.
Makes 10 appetizers.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Combine whipped topping mix with 1 cup of milk and vanilla in a large mixer bowl.
Beat on high with electric mixer, about 6 minutes or until topping thickens and forms peaks.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Blend on low; beat on high for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pie shell.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Pour chocolate chips into bottom of pie shell.
Mix other ingredients together well and pour over chips.
Bake 1 hour or until middle of pie does not wobble.
Also good when butterscotch chips are substituted for chocolate chips.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Pour all ingredients into a slow cooker.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with fruit and bread for a well-rounded meal! Makes 6 servings.

title: sugar-free pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baked pie shell. Chill before serving.

title: cherry nut bars
directions: Combine the flour, oatmeal, sugar, chopped pecans, baking soda and sweet cream butter in a blender or food processor and mix. Reserve 1 1/2 cups mixture for topping.
Press remainder into 9 x 13-inch pan, evenly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: brie with garlic bread
directions: Remove wrapper from cheese, but not the skin.
Put in a glass bowl and microwave until melted.
While the Brie is melting, cut the loaf of bread lengthwise.
Butter bread and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Toast the bread until crispy.
Slice each long piece into single slices.
Serve bread around the dish with the melted cheese for dipping.
A good snack.

title: tiffany's pork butt
directions: Roll pork butt in pepper until thoroughly coated with black pepper.
Prepare charcoal in covered grill, in a circle; arrange charcoal when hot so butt is not over coals.
Smoke butt approximately 30 minutes per pound, until separates from bones or until done.
Baste with sauce made of lemon juice, Moore's sauce and garlic powder during last 30 minutes on grill.
Cut and serve with favorite sauce.

title: banana party pie
directions: Prepare mix as directed for pie filling on box except using 1 3/4 cups milk.
Cover surface of pie filling with waxed paper or Saran Wrap; chill.
Mix until well blended; fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.
Slice bananas into crust.
Pour filling over bananas.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and beat.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sally lumm or muffins
directions: Sift together into bowl the first 4 ingredients and add milk, margarine, eggs and extract.
Beat until mixed.
Bake in muffin tins.

title: stew
directions: Place meat in the bottom of a large oven casserole.
Arrange vegetables on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water and pour over vegetables.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Long slow cooking makes its own delicious gravy.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have two 11 x 7-inch baking dishes ready. In a large saucepan cook onion in oil 5 minutes or until translucent.
Stir in chili powder, garlic powder and cumin.
Add cream cheese and cook over low heat, breaking cheese into chunks with a wooden spoon until melted.
Add chicken and salsa.
Stir over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes until hot.
Remove from heat. Stir in 1 1/4 cups of the Cheddar cheese and the olives.
Wrap tortillas, in stacks of 8, in foil.
Heat in oven 8 to 10 minutes until warm and pliable.
Spread 1/4 cup enchilada sauce over bottom of each baking dish.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture slightly below center of each warm tortilla.
Roll up from bottom and arrange seam side down in baking dishes.
(Can be made ahead up to this point, covered and refrigerated up to 3 days.)

title: breakfast pie
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Mix sausage and cheese and sprinkle over pie crust.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: lime yogurt pie(low-fat)
directions: Mix gelatin (in powder form) with yogurt. Blend in whipped topping and pour in crust.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: he-man casserole
directions: Brown steak cubes on all sides; add onion and garlic.
Cook until golden.
Stir in flour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Turn into greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours, until meat is tender.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: moussaka
directions: Cook beef in oil, remove beef.	Add more oil if needed and cook garlic, egg plant, scallions for 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and peppers, cook 5 minutes.
Add ketchup, wine, olives.
Simmer 5-8 minutes, add beef, heat.
Serve alone or on rice or pasta.

title: pancake mix
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, vanilla and enough milk to stir up batter.
Cook in oiled skillet until browned.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk; blend.
Add flour gradually. Fold in nuts and chips.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: mock chopped liver
directions: Slice onions and saute in the olive oil until caramelized; let cool.
Place all ingredients and the onions in a food grinder or blender; process until the consistency of pate.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: alfredo style noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain well and return to cooking pot.
Add the Ricotta cheese, yogurt, Parmesan cheese, margarine and pepper.
Toss well to mix.
Transfer to warm platter and serve with a cooked green vegetable or marinated vegetable salad.

title: ricotta egg biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well after each one.
Add Ricotta, mixing well, with lemon extract and nutmeg.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add this to creamy mixture a little at a time, beating one minute.
Gradually drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put cooked rice in pan first.
Then add chicken, broccoli and eggs.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over chicken rice mixture.
Top with sliced green olives and sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Pour half the batter into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at temperature on box.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water and cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating well after each addition.
Then beat the batter until it is smooth.
Beat egg whites until very stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour into three 8 or 9-inch cake pans, greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or bake in two square 9-inch pans, 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; add onion, green pepper and celery; cook until onion is transparent.
Meanwhile, cook potatoes in water to cover for 5 minutes.
Measure potato water; add boiling water to make 2 cups.
Add potatoes and water to saucepan.
Add tomatoes and liquid from clams; bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Season to taste with thyme, salt and pepper.
Add clams and heat.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 package of beef.
Shape into a large ball.
Cover with remaining chipped beef.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: 12 pound fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add orange juice.
Add flour gradually.
Mix thoroughly.
Flour fruit. Add to mixture.
Flour pecans and add last.
Mix well.
Grease and flour pans.
Line bottom of pans with brown paper.
Grease paper.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°; then 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 250°. Decorate top with pecans and cherries.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in heavy saucepan until well mixed.
Whisk in evaporated milk and egg yolks.
Place over medium heat; whisk in hot water slowly.
Cook, whisking constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens enough to stand a spoon in. Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut, butter and vanilla; and stir until smooth.

title: english ground beef curry
directions: Cook onion in Dutch oven.
Add and brown hamburger.
Drain excess fat.
Add beans and raisins.
Chop apple into small pieces and add along with brown sugar.
Mix 1 cup of water and curry powder, then add.
Cover and cook on low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans in salted water; drain if using canned beans and omit salt.
Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour over beans.
Add onions.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Garnish with onions and bake 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Combine shortening, egg and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Mix lightly. Spread in well-greased and floured pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° (appears soft when removed from oven, but will firm).
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: crabmeat and bacon rolls
directions: Combine tomato juice and egg. Add crumbs, seasonings, parsley, celery leaves and crabmeat.
Mix thoroughly. Roll into finger lengths and wrap each roll with 1/2 slice of bacon.
Fasten with toothpick. Broil, turning frequently, until evenly browned.

title: sweet cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries.
Add sliced bananas.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar to milk and mayonnaise and mix well.
This will be a very soft dough.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° until brown, about 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen rolls.

title: foolproof meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form. Gradually add marshmallow cream, beating until stiff peaks form. Spread over pie and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until meringue is browned.

title: spiced diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Beat pumpkin, milk and eggs.
Add other ingredients and beat together.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 350° for about 40 minutes.
Spices may be adjusted to individual taste.

title: easy cheesy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese; mix well. In iron skillet, shape half the mixture into a circle. Cut 4 slices of cheese into strips; arrange on meat. Top with remaining meat; press edges together to seal. Bake 1 hour; pour off fat. Top with remaining cheese. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and oranges.
Mix enough water to make 2 cups.
Cook until thick and clear.
Cool.
Pour over fruit. Mix well.
Keep in the refrigerator overnight.
Add bananas, just before serving.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar with oil and then add eggs.
Sift flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and allspice.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add baby food prunes and mix well.
Add nuts and mix thoroughly.

title: top ramen salad
directions: Chop up cabbage and onions.
Roast almonds and sesame seed in oven at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Break up Top Ramen in bowl with cabbage and onions.
Mix in seeds and almonds after roasting.

title: lisa's apple muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg.
Beat together.
Stir together dry ingredients and add to the first 4 ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Add apples and milk gently. Fill greased muffin cups and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: california quiche lorraine
directions: Crust:
Cut the butter into the flour; add the salt and egg and mix until dough holds.
Roll out on lightly floured board. Flute and prick; fill with wax paper and rice and bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
This will be pale.
(Discard paper and rice.)

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: milka's shipwreck stew
directions: Place raw sliced potatoes in 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Crumble browned hamburger over top.
Slice onion thin and put on top.
Top with beans and juice.
Spread tomato soup (undiluted) over top and bake, covered, for 1 hour and 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: salami roll
directions: Roll out dough.
If using crescent rolls or pizza rolls, seal triangles together.
First layer salami or pepperoni on dough and overlap each slice.
Then lay cheese on top.
Roll up lengthwise and cook according to directions on roll package.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add other ingredients except nuts.
Mix well; add nuts.
Bake in a greased tube pan for one hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Cut
bacon and fry; drain.
Saute onions.
Drain 3-bean salad and
combine all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: easy fish
directions: Wrap fish fillets in aluminum foil, but leave small opening at top.
Put on dash of sesame oil, soy sauce and sherry.
Then top with green onions and ginger to taste.
Fill large frypan about 1/4 full with water.
Put in fish in foil; cover to steam, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Delicious!

title: hot cereal
directions: Heat milk and water; do not boil.
Add oats and farina, stirring with wooden spoon until thickened.
Add honey to taste.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Cream well.
Add vanilla, lemon extract and almond extract and mix well. Sift flour and baking soda into the mixture.
Blend in sour cream. Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake in 9 to 10-inch tube pan, greased and floured, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage cheese bites
directions: Mix Bisquick and sausage to a coarse crumb mixture.
Add grated cheese.
Form into balls. Cook on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Beat the eggs well.
Fry bread crumbs in butter.
Add eggs, crumbs, flour, salt, onion and parsley (if using) to the mashed potatoes.
Drop into boiling salt water and cook for 20 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Put in crock pot. Stir and cook all day!
Really good with cornbread.

title: macaroni and ham loaf
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs and let stand.
Mix ingredients together and shape into a loaf.
Put in a pan and bake, in a pan of water, for 2 hours, in a slow oven, or 1 hour at 350°.

title: oreo cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Crush package of Oreos; add butter.
Save 1/2 cup for topping.
Press remainder into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: oreo delight
directions: First, you crush up the Oreos in bits of pieces.
Then you pour chocolate syrup on top of the Oreos.
Add the ice cream and Cool Whip.
Then you pour some more chocolate syrup.
Put it in the freezer to cool.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spread potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Let thaw.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over potatoes.
May be topped with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 people.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: johnnie cake-bahaman style
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, cutting in shortening.
Add milk and mix.
Press out and put in a greased pan.
Bake in oven at 400°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, raisins, bacon and onion in bowl. Combine mayo, sugar and vinegar; mix into other ingredients just before serving. Garnish with almonds.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Wash raisins in hot water.
Set aside.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
