Add beaten eggs, milk, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; mix.

title: spiced apple twists
directions: Pour orange juice in bottom of buttered 9-inch square baking pan.
Unroll crescent roll dough; separate into eight triangles. Cut each lengthwise to make 16 triangles.
Cut each apple into eight pieces.
Place on apple slice at wide end of each strip; roll up.
Arrange in pan.
Drizzle butter over tops, then sprinkle with combined cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden in color.
Serve warm or cold.
Fast and easy! Kirstie likes these!

title: fried squash
directions: Peel squash and cut in 1/4 inch round slices, dip in milk then coat with cornmeal. Fry.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl with a wire whisk.
Pour into greased baking dish.
I use a brownie pan.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake in pan of water at 350° approximately 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender container and process until smooth.
(It is not recommended making it without a blender in which recipes require consistency.)
It can be stored in refrigerator up to three days, but can be used immediately.
When used in puddings or pie fillings like the original, it will thicken when adding lemon or lime juice (add lemon or lime extract to compensate).
Makes about 1 3/4 cups or amount needed when recipes calls for a 14 ounce can of sweetened condensed milk.

title: chicken salad balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill several hours. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Yields about 2 dozen.
A satisfying summer salad.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine
dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring
until
dry
ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and banana.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Whip egg and add all ingredients except flour.
Mix well, then stir in flour.
Roll out on a floured surface and let dry 4 hours. Cut into strips and add to hard boiling chicken broth.

title: pancakes
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring until blended, but still slightly lumpy.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter on hot, greased pan.
Cook until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon margarine until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients with squash.
Pour into greased baking dish. Spread topping on mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: *easy divinity frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, except marshmallows and vanilla.
Put in the top of a double boiler.
With an electric mixer, beat for 7 minutes over boiling water.
Turn beater off and blend in the marshmallows.
Continue beating for about 2 minutes longer or until marshmallows are completely dissolved.
Remove from heat and add vanilla; blend well.
Icing now should be ready to use.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine Apple and Orange Juice Concentrate in a bowl; toss well.
Stir in Celery, Walnuts and Raisins.
Fold in Whipped Topping.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
6 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Generously grease a 12-cup muffin tin. Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices.
Quickly stir together both mixtures.
Fold in raisins and walnuts.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 18 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Remove from oven and let cool a few minutes.
Serve warm with butter or honey butter.

title: petite cherry cheesecakes
directions: Beat together first five ingredients until light and fluffy. Line small muffin pans with baking cups.
Place a small vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Fill 2/3 full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break rolls into small pieces.
Sprinkle with water to moisten.
Add margarine, eggs, sugar, raisins, pecans and small amount of orange peel; mix well.
Spray baking dish with Pam. Fill dish with mixture and bake at 350° until desired browning. Serve warm.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Roll up chicken in crescent rolls. You may substitute canned biscuits.
Place in a baking dish (use Pam or oil).
Mix cream of chicken soup, broth, milk and cheese in a sauce pan.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chinese-fried chicken wings
directions: Cut off wing tips at joints; discard these.
Cut other sections at joint, also.
Mix eggs, milk, flour, soy sauce and salt. Dip pieces of chicken in batter and fry in hot deep oil, 350° on frying thermometer.
Fry Daddy type until hot and crisp. Drain on paper towels; may need to sprinkle more salt.
Makes about 32 pieces.

title: roquefort salad dressing
directions: Mix with beaters for 3 minutes and then chill.

title: heavenly hash(dessert)
directions: Drain crushed pineapple and cherries.
Whip cream.
Add fruit, nuts, vanilla and enough marshmallows to absorb cream.
Place in sherbet glasses.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Serves 12.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta with eggs.
Add salt and pepper.
Boil lasagna in 4 quarts of salted water to which 1 tablespoon of oil has been added.
(Oil keeps lasagna from sticking together.)
Cook for 15 minutes; drain.
Slightly cover bottom of casserole dish with meat sauce, then alternate layers as follows:
lasagna, Ricotta, lasagna, sauce, etc., ending with lasagna.
Top with layer of sliced Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with tomato sauce.
Bake in moderate oven for about 30 minutes.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: congealed blackberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice until it boils.
Pour over jello. When dissolved and cooled, add buttermilk.
Put in refrigerator. When partially congealed, fold in Cool Whip and nuts, if desired. Refrigerate to mold.
Mold in a small ring mold.
Unmold on lettuce; fill center with cottage cheese and top with cherry.

title: pickled banana peppers
directions: Clean and cut peppers; let stand in scalding water for 5 minutes.
In each jar put 2 cloves of garlic, 1/2 teaspoon pickling salt and pinch of alum.
Boil 5 minutes:
2 cups white vinegar, 2 cups water and 1 cup sugar.
Pour into stuffed jars and seal.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Keep covered and refrigerated (will keep for 6 weeks).
Use as needed.
Bake at 400° about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bread custard pudding
directions: Combine crumbs and milk.
Bring to boiling point.
Add butter.
Stir into eggs and sugar, beaten light, in pudding dish. Flavor with vanilla.
Add raisins.
Surround dish or individual custard cups with hot water and bake in a moderate 350° oven until brown or until knife inserted comes out clean, about 1 hour.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix together the sugar and eggs.
Then blend well along with the
oil.
Mix
or sift (sift, what's that?) dry ingredients together
(flour,
soda,
salt
and
cinnamon).
Add dry ingredients
to
oil mixture.
Then add vanilla, pineapple (do not drain) and carrots.
Combine all these ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 53 minutes. Makes 3 layers.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies including frosting in blender.
Add melted butter.
Keep 2 cups crumbs for topping.
Press remaining mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Slice ice cream and place on mixture.
Let soften and spread evenly.
Spread sauce on ice cream and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining cookie mixture on top and put in freezer.
Remove and let stand several minutes before cutting and serving.

title: uncle tom's famous sloppy joes
directions: Quick, easy and tasty.
Brown ground beef in frypan.
Pour off fat.
Add equal parts of ketchup and both barbecue sauces until you have a sloppy juicy mixture.
Warm until sauce bubbles rapidly.
Serve on hamburger buns.
One pound makes about 6 servings.

title: peachy keen slush
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar and 2 cups water. Mix well. Bring to boil. Boil 3 minutes. Set aside.

title: homemade chili mac
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Cook macaroni and mix in with hamburger.
On low heat add all other ingredients to hamburger-macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle
chili powder to taste and ketchup, too.
Melt cheese into pot.
Heat and serve.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix cheese and butter.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: wacky cocoa cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Let cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into a uncooked pie shell and bake for 15 minutes at 425.
Reduce heat to 350 and bake for an additional 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix these ingredients well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan, pressing in bottom and sides.
Save a little for the top.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix all together; put in a long cake pan and bake 1 hour or until done.

title: powdered sugar cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix all well.
Grease and flour a large tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tenderloin tips
directions: Mix together; pour over meat.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add salt, pepper, catsup and tomato sauce.
Put into an 8-inch dish.
Cut cheese into thin strips; lay on top of meat.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until biscuits are brown.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine water and butter in saucepan. Bring to boiling point. Add flour and salt all at once.
Stir until in a big wad and leaves the side of pan.
Take pan off the heat. Add eggs, two at a time.
Use a hand mixer.
Beat the mixture until smooth after each addition.
Spoon onto greased baking sheet.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a well greased oblong casserole.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 1/2 stick butter over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss pickles
directions: Green and red sweet peppers may be used in any proportion. Discard seeds.
Put peppers through food chopper twice, using the finest knife.
Measure peppers.
Use enough juice from peppers to make cups level.
Add sugar and vinegar and mix thoroughly.
Heat rapidly to a full rolling boil.
Stir constantly before and while boiling.
Boil hard for 2 minutes.
Remove from fire and stir in fruit pectin.
Stir and skim alternately for just 8 minutes to cool slightly to prevent floating.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 9 ingredients in dish.
Put a layer of mayonnaise over top.
Then put cherry tomatoes on top, cover with plastic wrap and chill overnight.
When time to serve, toss and mix.
You can change vegetables to your taste.
Top with the shredded cheese.

title: lite and lean stuffed cabbage
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Boil a pot of water.
Take core out of cabbage and blanch.
Remove cabbage leaves, one by one. Mix all other ingredients together, except tomato soup.
Place ground chicken
in
cabbage
leaf;
wrap it and place in pan. Pour tomato
soup
over	cabbage
rolls.
Wrap foil over pan. Place in oven for 1 hour.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: In large bowl mix all ingredients well.
Pour into crust.
Let set in icebox at least 3 to 4 hours.
You can use different flavors like pineapple juice and crushed pineapple.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in 6-cup buttered casserole.
Place in slow oven (300°) about 3 hours until pudding is thick and creamy, not dry.
Stir every 15 minutes for 2 hours, carefully turning under brown top and scraping edges down.
Sprinkle with nutmeg (optional) when done.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash berries. Boil cup of water. Mix dry ingredients, sugar, cornstarch & Jell-O. Pour boiling water into dry ingredients & cook over medium heat until thickened, about 5 minutes. Place berries in pie crust. Pour cooked mixture over berries. Place in refrigerator to chill. Top with Cool Whip.

title: crab cakes
directions: Heat a little olive oil or peanut oil in skillet and heat. Combine above ingredients in bowl.
Make patties.
Roll in flour and brown both sides.
It helps to keep hands moist while making the patties.
For a change in flavor, you can add 1/4 tsp. curry powder, 1/8 tsp. turmeric and 1/2 tsp cumin.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fudge
directions: In a large bowl, put Toll House chips, walnuts, butter and vanilla.
In a heavy saucepan, put sugar, milk and marshmallows. Bring to boil the sugar, milk and marshmallows.
Boil exactly
6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into bowl of chocolate chip mixture and stir until chips are melted.
Pour into pan lined with wax paper.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook beef, drain. Add Ragu and simmer. You will need 8 medium to large cabbage leaves, keeping each leaf in one piece, immerse, four at a time into boiling water about 3 minutes or until limp. drain well. Place about 1/3 cup meat mixture on each leaf, fold in sides. Starting at an unfolded edge, carefully roll up each leaf, making sure folded sides are included in roll. Combine the tomato sauce, sugar, and dried basil. Pour half the sauce mixture into the baking dish. Add cabbage rolls. Spoon remaining tomato mixture on top. Bake, covered in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: apple nest
directions: Peel apples and place in 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Mix ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix well.
Keep in tight containers and use as needed.
Just add water or milk to the amount you use right away.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream cheese and butter together at room temperature.
Work in flour.
Line baking sheets with aluminum foil.
Using a cookie press with the star tip, press dough onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into desired length.
Store in an airtight container.

title: italian chocolate cookies
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Cut in 2 cups Crisco as you would for pie crust, until crumbly.
Add and mix in rest of ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Shape into small balls.
Bake in a 375° oven for 9 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the eggs, sugar, butter and Crisco.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add flavorings, continuing to blend on low speed of mixer.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stir-fried chicken
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and marinate thinly sliced chicken in it, at least 1 hour.
Stir-fry vegetables.
Add chicken with marinade.
Cook thoroughly.
May add water if necessary.
Serve over rice.

title: spice cupcakes
directions: In a saucepan, bring water and raisins to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside (DO NOT DRAIN).
In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and raisins.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups with 1/3 c. batter each.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until cupcakes test done.
Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pan to a wire rack.
For frosting, combine brown sugar, half-and-half and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium-low heat; cook and stir until smooth.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Stir in powdered sugar until smooth.
Frost cupcakes; top with coarsely chopped walnuts, if desired.
Makes 14 cupcakes.

title: saucy applesauce cake
directions: Mix as given.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Grease tube pan with 1/2 of cinnamon mixture.
Pour half of batter in pan.
Put rest of cinnamon mixture over cake.
Put other half of batter over this and bake at 350° until it tests done.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt in microwave.
Keep heated in crock-pot.

title: quick pizza
directions: Spread the bread with tomato soup.
Put on the pepperoni slices and top with cheese.
Bake in toaster oven until brown or the microwave for 45 seconds.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts and chill several hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Put cabbage in hot salted water to loosen leaves.
Mix hamburger, onion, rice, salt and pepper.
Roll into balls about the size of an egg.
Wrap with one or two cabbage leaves.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish and cover with water and tomatoes.
Cook tightly covered in moderate oven (350°) for 2 hours.
During last half hour of cooking, add 1 cup sweet cream.

title: fruit crisp with streusel topping
directions: Arrange peeled, sliced apples in baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Place rolled oats, flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon in a bowl and mix until well blended.
Add soft butter or margarine and blend well with pastry blender or fork.
Spread oatmeal mixture on top of apples and press down lightly.
Preheat oven to moderate heat (350°).
Make sure rack is in the center position in the oven. Bake about 30 minutes or until topping is brown and apples are tender when tested with a fork.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix together corn meal, milk, soda, salt, eggs and creamed corn and set aside.
Brown hamburger with green chilies, onion and garlic.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/2 corn mixture, 1/2 meat mixture, then 1/2 cheese.
Repeat first 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then top with remaining cheese.

title: chicken cutlet casserole
directions: Mix together cream of chicken soup with the required heavy cream and half and half in a casserole dish.
Add the chicken cutlets.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over noodles.
Delicious!

title: apple rice pork chops
directions: Dredge pork chops in flour, salt, pepper and cloves.
Brown chops on both sides in butter in large skillet.
Add 1/2 cup apple juice; cover and simmer until chops are tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Keep chops warm in serving platter.
Bring remaining juice to boil; stir in rice.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in applesauce.
Place chops on rice to serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: uncle bud's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in medium saucepan over low heat.
Stir until hot.
Use to baste meat in last stage of cooking and as sauce when serving.

title: derby day cheese grits
directions: Prepare grits in water with salt according to instructions on box.
After grits have cooked, add cheese, milk, eggs and margarine.
Mix. Pour into 13 x 10 x 2-inch casserole dish (4 1/2-quart white French Corning is perfect).
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir the bananas, applesauce and honey together.
You may use an electric mixer for this recipe, but it is not necessary.
Stir the dry ingredients together, then add them to the liquid mixture, stirring until the flour is moistened.
Add the almonds and stir.

title: 24 hour slaw or sissa's slaw
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients until dissolved, but do not heat. Chop cabbage, pepper and onion.
Pour over chopped vegetables.

title: frosted meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, 1/2 cup soup, bread, onion, egg, salt and pepper. Shape into loaf; place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost loaf with mashed potatoes.
Bake 15 minutes more. Blend remaining soup, water and drippings.
Heat.
Pour over meat and potatoes or serve in a bowl.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven in either mini or regular muffin pans, greased and floured.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Combine chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots and add drained squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix with butter (save a small amount of stuffing mix to sprinkle on top and spread on bottom of baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Drain. Cool. Add other ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate 12 hours. Serve cold.

title: italian  sausage stuffed apples
directions: Break up sausage in skillet; cook slowly with onion until meat is browned. Drain off fat.

title: skillet macaroni and cheese with tomatoes
directions: Whisk milk and cornstarch in a medium-size nonstick saucepan until blended.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring often. Stir in mustard, salt and hot pepper sauce until blended.
Reduce heat to medium heat and simmer, covered, 1 minute or until thickened.
Stir in cheeses until melted.
Stir in macaroni, tomatoes and scallions; heat through.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Coat the bottom and sides of large roasting pan with nonstick vegetable spray.
Place popped corn in roasting pan.
In a heavy pan, slowly melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake, without stirring in a tightly covered 2-quart casserole for 45 minutes at 350° or until rice is no longer soupy.
Remove cover and toss rice with a fork as seasonings come to the top.
Needs no gravy.
May be frozen after baking.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Put chips in bottom of pan.
Pour 1 cup of chicken broth over chips, then add chicken.
Mix cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups together with Ro-Tel.
Pour over chicken.
Top with Cheddar cheese soup.
You can add extra shredded cheddar cheese if you like.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in 9-inch pie shells. Chill before serving.

title: macaroni and beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions.
Rinse and drain. Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper in a skillet.
Do not drain.
Stir in flour and add tomatoes and cook until mixture thickens.
Stir in cheese, seasonings and macaroni.
Spoon into buttered 3 quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until hot and golden brown.

title: fruit ambrosia
directions: Peel and cut each grape in half and remove seeds.
Peel oranges; section and remove all white membranes.
Cut each section of orange "meat" in half.
Each chunk of orange should be about 1/4 inch.
Add pineapple, pecans, sliced bananas and sugar.
Mix well.
This should be real juicy.
Serve in glass dessert dishes with sweetened whipped cream on top.
We serve this at Christmas with pound cake.

title: chicken rice dinner(serves 5)
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, chestnuts and celery.
Lightly grease 3-quart casserole.
Lay breasts in pan.
Pour over mixed ingredients.
Mix stuffing with melted butter and sprinkle on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: whole wheat cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar, milk, soda and powder together. Melt butter in a 9 x 13 pan in a 350° oven. Pour flour mixture in pan with melted butter. Put the fruit on top of the flour mixture and bake for 30 minutes.

title: cajun corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 2 corn bread pans or 18 muffin cups.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into large bowl.
With a fork, blend in cornmeal. Add remaining ingredients to bowl. Stir just until all dry ingredients are moist.
Do not overbeat.
Pour batter into greased hot pan.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Combine ingredients into 2 qt. casserole.
Top with potato chips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: best tomato catsup
directions: Measure spices into small saucepan; add vinegar.
Cover; heat to a boil.
Remove from heat; let stand while you prepare tomato mixture.
(Spices steep in vinegar, just like tea.
This brewing keeps catsup rich red in color.)
Wash tomatoes.
Mash in large pan.
Add onion and red pepper.
Heat to a boil; cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put tomatoes through food mill or coarse sieve.
Add sugar to the tomato juice.
Heat to a boil, then simmer briskly.
Cook until you have only half the amount you began with. (Measure amount now with a ruler so you won't have to guess later.) It will take about 45 to 60 minutes.
Strain spiced vinegar mixture into tomato mixture; discard spices.
Add salt.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Fill hot, sterilized jars; seal at once. Makes 2 pints.

title: grandma bea's brownies
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs to creamed mixture.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add melted chocolate and nuts.
Grease bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and salt.
Add melted butter and buttermilk.
Stir in coconut and vanilla.
Pour in pie shells. Bake at 350° until brown and center does not shake.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Season and brown ground meat.
Drain.
Mix cornbread per package instructions.
Add corn, onion and meat.
Shred cheese and add.
Chop jalapenos and add.
Mix well.
Spray pan (9 x 13-inch) with Pam.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 375°
for 30 to 45 minutes. Stick middle to see if done.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt margarine; add milk, sugar, coconut and pecans.
Mix well. Chill before making balls.
Chill after you roll balls.
In double boiler, melt together paraffin wax and chocolate chips.
When melted, dip balls of candy into chocolate mixture using a toothpick.
Put onto foil-lined tray.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Using half can of both soups, mix with chicken, green chilies, half of the cheese and sour cream. Roll into flour tortillas.
Mix rest of soup with 1/2 cup milk. Pour over enchiladas.
Sprinkle rest of cheese over. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: coon and fixins'
directions: After dressing out coon, cut into small pieces and salt to taste. Cook in the inset of pressure cooker for about an hour at 15 pounds pressure. Cook longer if it is an old and tough coon. When coon is tender, arrange pieces in baking dish; cover with dressing made like this here...

title: fudge sauce
directions: Heat butter and chocolate in top of double boiler until melted. Stir in salt, then sugar in 4 or 5 portions being sure to blend in sugar thoroughly after each portion. The mixture becomes very thick, dry and grainy. Stir in milk very slowly. Cook 5-6 minutes longer or until slightly thickened, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.

title: ken's macho baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Melt butter and saute onions in butter and drippings. Add brown sugar, chili sauce, garlic powder, ketchup, mustard, barbecue sauce, Worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce, Triple Sec and salt.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Add beans and 12 pieces of crumbled bacon.
Mix and pour into baking dish.
Add liquid smoke to taste (lots!).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until beans are moist but not runny.
Garnish with remaining 4 pieces of bacon, crumbled.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift together all dry ingredients and then add to the creamed mixture. Scoop out by tablespoon and roll into balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork before baking. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate chip treasure cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a small bowl, mix cracker crumbs, flour and

baking powder. In a mixer bowl, beat the sweetened milk and butter until smooth. Add the flour mixture and mix well. Stir in coconut, chocolate chips and walnuts. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets. Bake 9 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool 2 or 3 minutes; remove from sheets. Makes 3 dozen.

title: hershey pie
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows until melted.
Add Hershey bar; stir until well blended.
Cook thoroughly; fold in 8 to 10 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust or baked pie crust. Chill until firm.

title: oil pastry
directions: Mix well.
Makes pastry for one pie.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla, eggs (one at a time), syrup and nuts, if desired.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.
Melt butter, cream and sugar.
Bring to a boil and add chocolate chips.
Pour on hot cake.
Can be refrigerated and reheated.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Peel and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine rest of ingredients except chips; pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with potato chips before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar gradually. Add well beaten egg.
Add sifted flour and other dry ingredients. Drop on cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork which has been dipped in flour and make a crisscross on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pastor schmidt's hamburger barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Melt together in microwave (or in saucepan on stove).
Mix into hamburger in a bowl.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Form into patties and broil over medium charcoal fire.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over oatmeal and let stand while you mix the other ingredients.
Cream all other ingredients together.
Add oatmeal and water mixture; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: *To make sour milk, add 1 teaspoon lemon juice to 1/2 cup whole or skim milk.
Let stand 5 minutes before using.

title: lasagne o'lay
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in frypan.
Blend in blender taco seasoning, Mexican tomatoes, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add to beef and cook for 30 minutes.
Spray 13 x 9-inch glass Pyrex or cake pan with Pam.
Cut flour tortillas in 1-inch strips and layer on bottom of pan.
Add 1/2 meat sauce.
Grate 1/2 of Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Add 1/2 carton of sour cream.
Repeat with tortilla strips remaining, meat sauce, sour cream and ending with cheese topping.
Bake at 350° until hot in middle.
Let stand for 10 minutes and decorate top with black olives.

title: marinade for beef strips
directions: Marinate meat for 1/2 hour.
Cook on grill.
Very good.

title: crystallized nuts
directions: Combine sugar, cream, butter, cinnamon	and
salt
in 2 quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and continue cooking, stirring constantly until
mixture	reaches
on candy thermometer (firm ball stage).
Remove
from
heat;
add vanilla, caramel flavor and nuts.
Spread
on
cookie sheet to cool.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil and shell eggs and stick four cloves into each egg.
Heat the vinegar and when boiling, add salt, pepper and mustard mixed with a little cold vinegar.
Put the eggs in a glass fruit jar and pour the boiling vinegar over them.
Cover and let stand for 2 weeks before using.
Serve with broiled steak.

title: choco peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine until fluffy.
Blend in water, egg substitute and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour and baking soda; mix well. Cover; chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using bottom of glass, dipped in sugar, press into 1/4 inch thick circle.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove and put on rack; cool.
Melt chocolate pieces.
Stir in shortening.
Top each cookie with chocolate; let cool.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: christmas custard
directions: Mix pudding mix with part of milk; beat.
Add whipping cream and sugar and beat again.
Add rest of milk or to the consistency you want.
You can add a little rum to it, if you like.
Store in refrigerator and shake before serving.

title: festive pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until set in middle.
This freezes well for weeks.

title: charles' corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix; bake at 400° until golden brown (approximately 30 minutes).
Cut in squares.
Serve hot.
If there should be a square leftover, it is just as good warmed over and served the next day.

title: 7-up fruit mold
directions: Cream the last 3 ingredients.
Drain fruits.
Mix together gelatin with tap water.
Add hot water, then 7-Up, Sprite or ginger ale.
Mix together with the creamed ingredients.
Grease mold with mayonnaise and pour into pan, then add drained fruits on top, spreading evenly.
(You may want to slice peaches into smaller pieces.)
Chill.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Beat egg with milk and add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir with a fork just until all is moist (lumpy is okay).
Add berries and stir quickly.
Fill well-greased muffin tins half full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes about 20 muffins.
Freeze well.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in saucepot, cook spaghetti as label directs.
Drain.
Return to saucepot.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: liver - n - onions
directions: Wash liver.
Heat large skillet and oil.
Flour liver.
Cook very slow.
Take liver out.
Pour in onions.
Cook.
Pour in 1/2 cup water.
Add liver.
Cover.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: rich and moist coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes down through cake with utility fork.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers (get seeds out).
Mix with sugar and vinegar on low heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil; stir. Stir while comes to a full rolling boil.
When rolling boil, boil 2 minutes.
Remove from fire; add food coloring and Certo.
Cool a minute or 2; pour in jelly glasses and seal.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush wafers, butter and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.
Spread softened ice cream over wafers.
Chill.
Top with fudge sauce.
Freeze approximately 10 hours.
Top with whipped cream and slivered almonds.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Mix rest of ingredients in. Mix well.
Press into large buttered cake pan.
Cut in squares and serve.
This makes a large amount.

title: white cookies
directions: Roll out thin. Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: glazed spiced orange slices
directions: Slice oranges 1/4-inch thick; discard ends.
Place orange slices in saucepan; add water to cover.
Cover pan; simmer for 30 minutes.
Drain, rinse well and return slices to pan.
Add sugar, vinegar, water, cloves and cinnamon.
Simmer for 1 hour, uncovered.
Orange slices should be tender and well glazed.
Pack slices in sterilized jars.
Fill with hot syrup and seal.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown together in skillet the hamburger, bacon and onions. Mix in 5-quart casserole the 4 cans of beans and do not drain the beans.
Add to casserole the remaining ingredients and meat mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill Pet milk overnight.
Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water.
Add sugar, grated rind and 4 tablespoons lemon juice. When mixture is slightly congealed, whip the milk and gradually add the gelatin mixture.
Add almond extract.
Line bottom of large casserole dish with crushed vanilla wafers. Pour mixture over wafers and sprinkle some of the wafers on top.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: tasty turkey pot pie
directions: Combine salad dressing, flour, bouillon and pepper in a medium saucepan.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly over low heat until thickened.
Add turkey and vegetables; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into an 8-inch square pan (or a 10 x 6-inch baking dish).

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 1 hour; stir twice.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Toss carrots, raisins and oranges together.
Moisten with mayonnaise and pile on mounds of shredded cabbage.
Garnish with chopped peanuts.
Serves 6.

title: linguini with white clam sauce
directions: Drain clam juice from clams and reserve.
Saute onion and garlic in oil and butter in a saucepan until tender, but not brown, about 5 minutes.
Add reserved clam juice, oregano, salt and pepper, and bring to boiling over high heat.
Cook until reduced to 1 cup, about 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook linguini following label directions and drain.
Keep hot in heavy pan. Lower heat under clam juice mixture, add clams, parsley, and lemon juice, and heat thoroughly.
Toss with hot linguini.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shell.
Put in freezer and let stay until it firms.
Slice and serve.
(Freezes well.)

title: weihnachtkuchen(fruit cake)
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients over fruit and nuts; mix until well coated.
Pour into loaf pan (bottom lined with waxed paper); bake in slow oven (275°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 2 to 3 days before cutting (after taking out of pan).

title: aunt feeny's chocolate cake
directions: Into a mixing bowl, sift together 3 times the dry ingredients. Make a well; add coffee, oil, egg and vanilla.
Beat to a smooth consistency.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven.
Coat with Fudge Frosting.
